Description: The impression of the foot in a soft substance such as sand or snow.

Name: LICK
Description: To stroke with the tongue.

Name: LAME
Description: Moving with pain or difficulty on account of injury, defect or temporary obstruction of a function.

Name: CHEW

Name: FIG

Name: FAT (ORGANIC SUBSTANCE)

Name: MANIOC FLOUR
Description: Flour made of the cassava plant or root.

Name: FELT

Name: CLOAK

Name: PONCHO

Name: GRASS-SKIRT

Name: STOCKING

Name: HEADBAND

Name: HEADDRESS
Description: A decorative covering or ornament worn on the head.

Name: RAG

Name: PLAIT

Name: COOKHOUSE

Name: MEETING HOUSE
Description: A building where people meet for a purpose.

Name: PADLOCK

Name: PITCHFORK

Name: RAKE

Name: DIGGING STICK

Name: LASSO

Name: SICKLE

Name: HAY

Name: VINE

Name: TREE TRUNK

Name: SAP

Name: BANYAN

Name: SORGHUM

Name: FISH POISON

Name: ACHIOTE

Name: MANGROVE

Name: TARO

Name: UNTIE

Name: STRIKE

Name: POUND

Name: CUT DOWN

Name: SHEARS

Name: HANG UP

Name: POTTER

Name: FAN (ACTION)

Name: PEG

Name: STRING

Name: DWELL (LIVE, RESIDE)

Name: SMEAR

Name: SPLASH

Name: LIMP

Name: RIDE
Description: To transport oneself by sitting on and directing an animal.

Name: SLEDGE

Name: OWE

Name: BARTER
Description: To exchange goods without involving money.

Name: PICK UP

Name: POINTED

Name: LONG AGO

Name: ONE TIME

Name: SNIFF

Name: FRAGRANT

Name: LOUD

Name: PINCH

Name: BLUNT

Name: WRINKLED

Name: BLAME

Name: GOVERN

Name: FREEMAN

Name: RESPECT (SOMEBODY)

Name: BATTLE-AXE

Name: SLING

Name: FISHNET

Name: FISH TRAP

Name: PUNISHMENT

Name: BLESS

Name: TABLET

Name: PIERCE

Name: PLANTAIN

Name: CHICHA

Name: UPPER LEG (THIGH)

Name: SPEAR (SOMEBODY)

Name: DRESS

Name: UNTRUTH

Name: CUP

Name: LATE

Name: LIP

Name: GROW

Name: PLATE

Name: DISH

Name: NOBLE

Name: COMPOUND

Name: CONDEMN

Name: DISAPPEAR

Name: MINISTER

Name: SHY

Name: MANNER
Description: Way of performing or effecting anything.

Name: KIDNEY

Name: DESCENDANTS

Name: CENTER

Name: THREE

Name: FIVE

Name: REVENGE

Name: CALF OF LEG

Name: CURE

Name: CRUEL

Name: LIFT

Name: MAIZE

Name: STRONG EFFECT

Name: LAST YEAR

Name: NEXT YEAR

Name: SPOT

Name: BACK OF HEAD

Name: GLUTTON

Name: HUMP

Name: INFLATED
Description: Exaggerated or made bigger.

Name: LOW VOICE

Name: TURBID

Name: MULTITUDE
Description: A large number of something.

Name: PALATE
Description: The palate is the roof of the mouth in humans and other mammals.

Name: POETRY

Name: SCANTY
Description: Somewhat less than is needed in amplitude or extent.

Name: SHUTTLE

Name: SPICY
Description: Of, pertaining to, or containing spice; or spicy flavour: Provoking a burning sensation due to the presence of chillies or similar hot spices.

Name: SPRUCE

Name: SUCKER

Name: SURFACE

Name: INFECTED

Name: COPULATE

Name: DILUTE

Name: DISLOCATE

Name: GROW UP

Name: HEW

Name: HINDER

Name: INFRINGE

Name: OFFEND

Name: PASS BY

Name: BROTHER (OF MAN)

Name: BROTHER (OF WOMAN)

Name: SISTER (OF MAN)

Name: SISTER (OF WOMAN)
Description: The sister of a woman.

Name: YOUNG (OF WOMAN)
Description: Young of a woman as opposed to young of a man.

Name: YOUNG (OF MAN)

Name: OLD (OF MAN)

Name: OLD (OF WOMAN)

Name: SPOIL (BECOME SPOILED)

Name: STING

Name: BOOT

Name: BROKEN

Name: CLOSED

Name: NAKED

Name: PIECE

Description: A person who has completed a study of medicine, and as such tries to diagnose and cure diseases in patients.

Name: SHELL
Description: A hard outer covering of an animal, as the hard case of a mollusk.

Name: DRIVER'S LICENSE
Description: Official document granting someone the authorisation to drive some vehicles.

Name: STRANGE
Description: Out of the ordinary.

Name: LIE (MISLEAD)
Description: To knowingly say something that is untrue.

Name: HIDE (CONCEAL)
Description: To put something in a place where it will be harder to discover or out of sight.

Name: COAT
Description: An outer garment covering the upper torso and arms.

Name: GLASS
Description: A hard, amorphous, inorganic, usually transparent, brittle substance made by fusing silicates, sometimes borates and phosphates, with certain basic oxides and then rapidly cooling to prevent crystallization.

Name: GRAIN
Description: Edible, starchy seeds of the grass family (Graminae) usable as food by man and his livestock.

Name: GRASS
Description: A very large and widespread family of Monocotyledoneae, with more than 10.000 species, most of which are herbaceous, but a few are woody. The stems are jointed, the long, narrow leaves originating at the nodes. The flowers are inconspicuous, with a much reduced perianth, and are wind-pollinated or cleistogamous.

Name: GRASSHOPPER
Description: A plant-eating insect with long back legs that can jump very high and makes a sharp high noise using its back legs or wings.

Name: GULF
Description: An inlet of the sea of large areal proportions, more indented than a bay and generally more enclosed.

Name: HAIL
Description: Precipitation in the form of balls or irregular lumps of ice.

Name: PORT
Description: Area of water next to the coast, often surrounded by thick walls, where ships and boats can be sheltered.

Name: HARVEST
Description: The crop gathered in a season.

Name: HEAT
Description: A form of energy that is transferred by a difference in temperature: it is equal to the total kinetic energy of the atoms or molecules of a system.

Name: HIGH TIDE
Description: The level of water when the tide is at its highest level.

Name: HILL
Description: A natural elevation of the land surface, usually rounded.

Name: HORSE
Description: A large animal with four legs of the Equus caballus species which people ride on or use for carrying things or pulling vehicles.

Name: HOSPITAL
Description: A place where people who are ill or injured are treated and taken care of by doctors and nurses.

Name: ICE
Description: The dense substance formed by the freezing of water to the solid state; it commonly occurs in the form of hexagonal crystals.

Name: PRECIPICE
Description: A very steep decline, typically found in the mountains or on shores.

Name: ANIMAL
Description: Any living organism characterized by voluntary movement, the possession of cells with noncellulose cell walls and specialized sense organs enabling rapid response to stimuli, and the ingestion of complex organic substances such as plants and other animals.

Name: INSECT
Description: A class of the Arthropoda typically having a segmented body with an external chitinous covering, a pair of compound eyes, a pair of antennae, three pairs of mouthparts, and two pairs of wings.

Name: IRON
Description: A malleable ductile silvery-white ferromagnetic metallic element with symbol Fe and atomic number 26, occurring principally in haematite and magnetite. It is widely used for structural and engineering purposes.

Name: ISLAND
Description: A land mass, especially one smaller than a continent, entirely surrounded by water.

Name: LAGOON
Description: A body of water cut off from the open sea by coral reefs or sand bars.

Name: LAKE
Description: An enclosed body of water, usually but not necessarily fresh water, from which the sea is excluded.

Name: LAMP
Description: A device that produces light, such as an electric lamp.

Name: LAND
Description: A specified geographical tract of the Earth's surface including all its attributes, comprising its geology, superficial deposits, topography, hydrology, soils, flora and fauna, together with the results of past and present human activity, to the extent that these attributes exert a significant influence on the present and future land utilization. (Source: WHIT)

Name: LEAD (CHEMICAL ELEMENT)
Description: A heavy toxic bluish-white metallic element with symbol Pb and atomic number 82 that is highly malleable; occurs principally as galena and is used in alloys, accumulators, cable sheaths, paints, and as a radiation shield.

Name: LEAF
Description: The main organ of photosynthesis and transpiration in higher plants, usually consisting of a flat green blade attached to the stem directly or by a stalk.

Name: LEATHER
Description: The dressed or tanned hide of an animal, usually with the hair removed.

Name: LIGHT (RADIATION)
Description: Electromagnetic radiation that is capable of causing a visual sensation. (Source: CED)

Name: LIVESTOCK
Description: Cattle, horses, and similar animals kept for domestic use especially on a farm.

Name: LIZARD
Description: Any reptile of the suborder Lacertilia, especially those of the family Lacertidae, typically having an elongated body, four limbs, and a small tail: includes the gechos, iguanas, chameleons, monitors, and slow worms.

Name: MARKET
Description: Place of commercial activity in which articles are bought and sold.

Name: MEAT
Description: The edible flesh of animals, especially that of mammals.

Name: MILK
Description: The whitish fluid secreted by the mammary gland for the nourishment of the young; composed of carbohydrates, proteins, fats, mineral salts, vitamins, and antibodies.

Name: MILL
Description: A mill is a device that breaks solid materials into smaller pieces by grinding, crushing, or cutting.

Name: MOSS
Description: Any plant of the class Bryophyta, occurring in nearly all damp habitats.

Name: MOTORCYCLE
Description: Single-track, two-wheeled motor vehicle.

Name: MOUNTAIN
Description: A feature of the earth's surface that rises high above the base and has generally steep slopes and a relatively small summit area.

Name: MUD
Description: A mixture of clay and/or silt with water to form a plastic mass with a particle size preponderantly below 0.06 mm diameter. It is deposited in low-energy environments in lakes, estuaries and lagoons. It may also be deposited in deep-sea environments. (Source: WHIT)

Name: MUSHROOM
Description: An organism belonging to a family of Basidiomycetes that are characterized by the production of spores on gills.

Name: MUSIC
Description: The artistic organisation of sounds or tones that expresses ideas and emotions through the elements of rhythm, melody, harmony and tonal colour.

Name: NEED (NOUN)
Description: The fact or an instance of feeling the lack of something.

Name: OAK
Description: Any tree of the genus Quercus in the order Fagales, characterized by simple, usually lobed leaves, scaly winter buds, a star-shaped pith, and its fruit, the acorn, which is a nut; the wood is tough, hard, and durable, generally having a distinct pattern.

Name: OCEAN
Description: The mass of water occupying all of the Earth's surface not occupied by land, but excluding all lakes and inland seas.

Name: ASH
Description: The incombustible matter remaining after a substance has been incinerated.

Name: PAINT (PIGMENTS)
Description: A mixture of pigment and a vehicle, such as oil or water, that together form a liquid or paste that can be applied to a surface to provide an adherent coating that imparts colour, protects the surface and/or gives the surface different features.

Name: PAPER
Description: Felted or matted sheets of cellulose fibers, formed on a fine-wire screen from a dilute water suspension, and bonded together as the water is removed and the sheet is dried.

Name: PASTURE
Description: Land covered with grass or herbage and grazed by or suitable for grazing by livestock.

Name: PETROLEUM
Description: A comparatively volatile liquid bitumen composed principally of hydrocarbon, with traces of sulphur, nitrogen or oxygen compounds; can be removed from the earth in a liquid state.

Name: SEAL
Description: A mammal belonging to the Pinnipedia, an order of aquatic placental mammals having a streamlined body and limbs specialized as flippers: includes seals, sea lions, and the walrus.

Name: PLAIN
Description: Level or rolling open land, usually at a low elevation.

Name: PLANT (VEGETATION)
Description: Any living organism that synthesizes its food from inorganic substances, possesses cellulose cell walls, responds slowly and often permanently to a stimulus, lacks specialized sense organs and nervous system, and has no powers of locomotion.

Name: PLASTIC
Description: A polymeric material (usually organic) of large molecular weight which can be shaped by flow; usually refers to the final product with fillers, plasticizers, pigments, and stabilizers included (versus the resin, the homogeneous polymeric starting material); examples are polyvinyl chloride, polyethylene, and urea-formaldehyde.

Name: POISON
Description: A substance which, when ingested, inhaled, or absorbed, or when applied to, injected into, or developed within the body, in relatively small amounts, may cause injury, harm, or destruction to organs, tissue, or life.

Name: POLICE
Description: Branch of the government which is charged with the preservation of public order, the promotion of public health and safety, and the prevention, detection, and punishment of crimes.

Name: PRICE
Description: The amount of money paid per unit for a good or service.

Name: RAIN (PRECIPITATION)
Description: Precipitation in the form of liquid water drops with diameters greater than 0.5 millimeters.

Name: REED
Description: Any of various types of tall stiff grass-like plants growing together in groups near water.

Name: REEF
Description: A line of rocks in the tidal zone of a coast, submerged at high water but partly uncovered at low water.

Name: RELIGION
Description: The expression of man's belief in and reverence for a superhuman power recognized as the creator and governor of the universe.

Name: BATTERY
Description: A cell or several cells connected together, each cell containing the essentials for producing voltaic electricity.

Name: BAY
Description: An open, curving indentation made by the sea or a lake into a coastline.

Name: RESIN
Description: Any of a class of solid or semisolid organic products of natural or synthetic origin with no definite melting point, generally of high molecular weight.

Name: BEE
Description: Any of the membranous-winged insects which compose the superfamily Apoidea in the order Hymenoptera characterized by a hairy body and by sucking and chewing mouthparts.

Name: RIVER
Description: A stream of water which flows in a channel from high ground to low ground and ultimately to a lake or the sea, except in a desert area where it may dwindle away to nothing.

Name: ROAD
Description: A long piece of hard ground that people can drive along from one place to another.

Name: ROCK
Description: Any aggregate of minerals that makes up part of the earth's crust. It may be unconsolidated, such as sand, clay, or mud, or consolidated, such as granite, limestone, or coal.

Name: RODENT
Description: Any of the relatively small placental mammals that constitute the order Rodentia, having constantly growing incisor teeth specialized for gnawing.

Name: ROOT
Description: The absorbing and anchoring organ of a vascular plant; it bears neither leaves nor flowers and is usually subterranean.

Name: SAND
Description: A loose material consisting of small mineral particles, or rock and mineral particles, distinguishable by the naked eye; grains vary from almost spherical to angular, with a diameter range from 1/16 to 2 millimeters.

Name: EARLY
Description: Before the expected time or towards the beginning of a time period.

Name: SCHOOL
Description: An institution or building at which children and young people receive education.

Name: MOUTH
Description: Opening in the lower half of a human face which is used for food ingestion and articulation.

Name: FAECES (EXCREMENT)
Description: Substance that human and animal bodies release from time to time as a little pile of waste remaining from digestion, after it has been collected in the colon.

Name: SHIT (DEFECATE)
Description: To excrete faeces from one's body through the anus.

Name: AXE
Description: A tool for felling trees or chopping wood consisting of a heavy metallic or stone head flattened to a blade on one side, and which is attached to a usually wooden handle.

Name: BEARD
Description: Facial hair of humans on the chin, cheeks and jaw.

Name: BRIGHT
Description: Emitting or reflecting light readily or in large amounts. [WN:679]

Name: BREAK (DESTROY OR GET DESTROYED)
Description: To divide or be divided into pieces and thereby damaged.

Name: DESTROY
Description: To damage beyond use or repair.

Name: SIDE
Description: The side of an object or person.

Name: PERSON
Description: A human being.

Name: OWN
Description: To have rightful possession of property, goods or capital.

Name: DECIDE
Description: To reach, make, or come to a decision about something.

Name: EASY
Description: Requiring little skill or effort; posing no difficulty.

Name: NOTHING
Description: Not anything.

Name: LUNG
Description: A biological organ that extracts oxygen from the air.

Name: BETWEEN
Description: In the position or interval that separates two things.

Name: BOTTOM
Description: The part furthest in the direction toward which an unsupported object would fall.

Name: SEASON
Description: One of the four equal periods into which the year is divided by the equinoxes and solstices, resulting from the apparent movement of the sun north and south of the equator during the course of the earth's orbit around it. These periods (spring, summer, autumn and winter) have their characteristic weather conditions in different regions, and occur at opposite times of the year in the N and S hemispheres.

Name: BRING
Description: To transport toward somewhere; to take something or somebody with oneself somewhere.

Name: FROM
Description: Starting at a given point in space or time.

Name: GET
Description: To get or obtain an item; to come into the possession of something.

Name: GO
Description: To get from one place to another by any means.

Name: STIR
Description: To stir two or more substances together.

Name: CONTAIN
Description: To contain or hold; have within.

Name: WISE
Description: Showing good judgement or the benefit of experience.

Name: SAD
Description: Feeling mentally uncomfortable because something is missing or wrong.

Name: CARRY
Description: To lift and bring to somewhere else; to transport by lifting.

Name: SLOW
Description: With low speed.

Name: CATCH
Description: To take hold of, especially in the hands, so as to seize or restrain or stop the motion of.

Name: SOON
Description: In a near future.

Name: CLEAN
Description: Not dirty.

Name: GO UP (ASCEND)
Description: To move from a lower to a higher position by walking or climbing.

Name: DARK
Description: Having an absolute or (more often) relative lack of light.

Name: REMEMBER
Description: To recall from memory.

Name: SHINE
Description: To emit light.

Name: TEACH
Description: To pass on knowledge and skills.

Name: WHEEL
Description: A circular object that spins around a central axe thereby allowing relatively low-friction movement.

Name: TALL
Description: Having a vertical extent greater than the average.

Name: RICH
Description: Possessing in abundance a particular trait.

Name: STEAL
Description: To take possession of property belonging to another without the consent of this owner; most typically when not observed, rather than by force.

Name: SEED
Description: A mature fertilized plant ovule, consisting of an embryo and its food store surrounded by a protective seed coat (testa).

Name: SHOUT
Description: To say something in a loud voice.

Name: GROAN
Description: To utter a low, guttural sound of frustration.

Name: SWEET
Description: Having the taste characteristic of sugar or honey.

Name: PAY
Description: To give money in exchange for goods or services.

Name: FIND
Description: To encounter something by accident or after searching for it.

Name: GOOD LUCK
Description: Something positive that happens to someone by chance.

Name: LOW
Description: Being in a position comparatively close to the ground.

Name: ATTACK
Description: The application of violent force to someone or something.

Name: PLACE (POSITION)
Description: A position or area in a space.

Name: READ
Description: To look at and interpret letters or other information that is written.

Name: OLD PERSON
Description: An older person (usually considered to be above the age of 60).

Name: WHILE
Description: A certain duration of time, a period of time.

Name: WHICH
Description: What one or ones (of those mentioned or implied).

Name: FIRST
Description: Having no predecessor. The ordinal number corresponding to one.

Name: DAWN
Description: A period of time at the beginning of the day shortly before sunrise during which the light gradually becomes stronger.

Name: SNAKE
Description: Any reptile of the suborder Serpentes, typically having a scaly cylindrical limbless body, fused eyelids, and a jaw modified for swallowing large prey.

Name: BEVERAGE
Description: Any one of various liquids for drinking.

Name: YOUR (SINGULAR)
Description: Belonging to the second person that is addressed by the first person.

Name: EARN
Description: To gain (success, payment) through applied effort or work.

Name: MAKE
Description: To create something by combining or assembling materials or parts or by changing it.

Name: OWL
Description: A solitary, mainly nocturnal bird of prey, belonging to the order Strigiformes; it has large forward-facing eyes and ears and a hawk-like beak, and it can turn its head 180 degrees around.

Name: YARD
Description: A small, usually uncultivated area adjoining or within the precincts of a house or other building.

Name: LIGHT (IGNITE)
Description: To start a fire or light a flame.

Name: THING
Description: That which is considered to exist as a separate entity, quality or concept.

Name: FEED
Description: To give food.

Name: SHIP
Description: A vessel propelled by engines or sails for navigating on the water, especially a large vessel that can not be carried aboard another, as distinguished from a boat.

Name: DRIVE
Description: To operate a vehicle.

Name: END (OF SPACE)
Description: Extreme part.

Name: END (OF TIME)
Description: The last or final part.

Name: EGG
Description: Egg (either fertilized or not) from domesticated birds, most commonly hens, seen as food.

Name: SHELF
Description: A flat, rigid, rectangular structure, fixed at right angles to a wall, and used to support, store or display objects.

Name: SHOP
Description: A place, especially a small building, for the retail sale of goods and services.

Name: BICYCLE
Description: A vehicle with two wheels in tandem, pedals connected to the rear wheel by a chain, handlebars for steering, and a saddlelike seat.

Name: SOW SEEDS
Description: To scatter or disperse seeds on a field.

Name: ENTER
Description: To go into.

Name: DROP
Description: The event of moving to a lower position due to the effect of gravity.

Name: SHRUB
Description: A woody perennial plant, smaller than a tree, with several major branches arising from near the base of the main stem.

Name: STORE
Description: An establishment, either physical or virtual, that sells goods or services to the public.

Name: PUPIL (STUDENT)
Description: A student under the supervision of a teacher or professor.

Name: HURRY
Description: To move or do something at a fast pace.

Name: DENY
Description: To refuse strongly and solemnly to own or acknowledge.

Name: DEPEND
Description: To be connected with something as a cause of existence or as a necessary condition.

Name: BUTTON
Description: A fastener consisting of a knob or disc that is passed through a slit in the adjacent material.

Name: HERON
Description: A long-legged, long-necked wading bird of the family Ardeidae.

Name: SILVER
Description: A very ductile malleable brilliant greyish-white element with symbol Ar and atomic number 47 having the highest electrical and thermal conductivity of any metal.

Name: KNOT
Description: A loop of string or any other long flexible material which cannot be untied without pulling part of the string through the loops.

Name: COVER
Description: To place something over or upon to conceal or protect.

Name: OUTSIDE
Description: In the open, not within a building, or outside of something in general.

Name: SKIN
Description: The tissue forming the outer covering of the vertebrate body: it consists of two layers, the outermost of which may be covered with hair, scales, feathers, etc. It is mainly protective and sensory in function.

Name: SUIT
Description: (Of an object) To be of the right size and shape so as to match another object.

Name: MOVE
Description: To change the location of an object.

Name: MENSTRUATION
Description: The period in the menstrual cycle when the endometrium is shed when conception did not take place.

Name: CORPSE
Description: A dead body.

Name: LUNCH
Description: Meal usually eaten at midday.

Name: ROOF
Description: The structure covering a building.

Name: EARRING
Description: A piece of jewelry worn on the ear.

Name: HAT
Description: An item of clothing intended to cover the head made from material hard enough to have a shape independant of the skull, and most commonly with a rim.

Name: BELT
Description: A clothing accessory, usually made of leather or heavy cloth, worn around the waist and used to support trousers or other articles of clothing.

Name: HAVE
Description: To be in possession (of an object).

Name: CABBAGE
Description: An edible plant, Brassica oleracea, with many varieties.

Name: TRUMPET
Description: A musical instrument in the brass family.

Name: TRUNK OF TREE
Description: The part of the body from the neck to the groin excluding the head and limbs.

Name: FLUTE
Description: A musical instrument of the woodwind family.

Name: SMOKE (EXHAUST)
Description: An aerosol, consisting of visible particles and gases, produced by the incomplete burning of carbon-based materials, such as wood and fossil fuels.

Name: PART
Description: A seperate unit of a larger whole.

Name: OUR
Description: Belonging to us; of us.

Name: FEAR (FRIGHT)
Description: An emotion experienced in anticipation of some specific pain or danger.

Name: DEFEAT
Description: An end to a struggle or contest that did not end in success.

Name: VICTORY
Description: An end to a struggle or contest that did end in success.

Name: SNOW
Description: The most common form of frozen precipitation, usually flakes or starlike crystals, matted ice needles, or combinations, and often rime-coated.

Name: STRONG
Description: Capable of producing great physical force.

Name: SAILCLOTH
Description: A large piece of fabric (as canvas) by means of which wind is used to propel a sailing vessel.

Name: SAIL
Description: To traverse or travel by ship on a body of water.

Name: SOAP
Description: A cleansing agent, manufactured in bars, granules, flakes, or liquid form, made from a mixture of the sodium salts of various fatty acids of natural oils and fats.

Name: PEOPLE
Description: A group of persons forming or belonging to a particular nation, class, ethnic group, country, family, etc.

Name: READY
Description: Prepared for immediate action or use.

Name: STRANGER
Description: Someone who is not known.

Name: BOIL (OF LIQUID)
Description: To be at a temperature (as a liquid) where it moves into the gaseous phase.

Name: BOIL (OF SKIN)
Description: A painful, local inflammation of the skin, caused by infection of a hair follicle. Usually, a hard core and pus are present.

Name: PEN
Description: A utensil, usually tubular in form, containing ink used to write or make marks.

Name: TROUT
Description: Fresh water salmon.

Name: NIPPLE
Description: The projection of a mammary gland from which, on female mammals, milk can be secreted.

Name: TESTICLES
Description: The male sex gland that produces sperm and male hormones, found in some types of animals and humans.

Name: JAW
Description: Either of the two opposable structures forming, or near the entrance to, the mouth.

Name: WRIST
Description: The flexible and narrower connection between the forearm and the hand.

Name: THIGH
Description: The area between the pelvis and buttocks and the knee.

Name: RIB
Description: One of the long curved bones which form the rib cage.

Name: ADAM'S APPLE
Description: A lump at the front of the neck.

Name: ANKLE
Description: A joint formed where the foot and the leg meet.

Name: WOMB
Description: The major female reproductive organ of most mammals, including humans. It is a large muscle enveloping the phoetus during pregnancy.

Name: SPINE
Description: The body part that consists of a row of vertebrae, that support the head and torso and that forms a canal for nerves.

Name: BLANKET
Description: A large cloth used for warmth and for sleeping.

Name: SKILLED
Description: Experienced and clever, professional.

Name: DRIP (FALL IN GLOBULES)
Description: To fall in globules or small portions, as water or other liquid.

Name: TROUSERS
Description: An item of clothing worn on the lower part of the body and covering both legs separately.

Name: LOCUST
Description: Migratory grasshoppers of the order Orthoptera of warm regions having short antennae.

Name: SOUL
Description: In philosophical or religious belief the immaterial part of a human being.

Name: SLAVE
Description: A person who is owned and forced to work, usually without pay, by another.

Name: DO
Description: To perform an action.

Name: DRESS UP
Description: To clothe oneself; to put on clothes.

Name: GOVERNMENT
Description: A body that has the authority to make and the power to enforce laws within a civil, corporate, religious, academic, or other organization or group.

Name: HALF
Description: One of the two equal parts of a whole.

Name: THEY
Description: The third person plural of the personal pronoun that designates more than one person or animal, thing or idea which have already been mentioned previously.

Name: WILLOW
Description: Any of various deciduous trees or shrubs in the genus Salix.

Name: STOMACH
Description: An organ in the body, involved in digestion of food.

Name: LAMB
Description: Young sheep.

Name: POPLAR
Description: Any of various deciduous trees of the genus Populus.

Name: HOW MANY
Description: Which quantity?

Name: SORCERER
Description: A male person who practices magic.

Name: WITCH
Description: A female person who practices magic.

Name: AWAKE
Description: Not sleeping.

Name: BRANCH (BIFURCATION)
Description: A separation of a river, a road, etc.

Name: ROLL
Description: To tip laterally.

Name: RACCOON
Description: (Procyon lotor) An omnivorous nocturnal mammal native to North America and Central America.

Name: RAFTER
Description: One of several parallel sloping beams that extend from the ridge to the wall-plate, to support the roof and its associated loads; the sloping top member of a roof truss, which carries the purlins.

Name: SOOT
Description: Impure black carbon with oily compounds obtained from the incomplete combustion of resinous materials, oils, wood, or coal.

Name: BASE
Description: The bottom or lowest part.

Name: BEAN
Description: Any of various leguminous plants grown for their edible seeds and pods.

Name: ENDURE
Description: To allow (something that one dislikes or disagrees with) to continue to exist or occur without interference; accept or undergo, often unwillingly.

Name: BUTTOCKS
Description: The fleshy part of the human body that one sits on.

Name: CHAPTER
Description: A part of a book, a literary work etc. with a distinct content, set apart using typography.

Name: SCREWDRIVER
Description: A hand tool used for driving screws.

Name: BLUE
Description: Having the pure color of a clear sky; the primary color between green and violet in the visible spectrum, an effect of light with a wavelength between 450 and 500 nm.

Name: REMAINS
Description: What remains after other things have been taken away (e.g. eaten or destroyed).

Name: ERR
Description: To make a mistake.

Name: CORMORANT
Description: Medium sized, black water bird from the family of the cormorants (Phalacrocoracidae), scientific name: Phalacrocorax carbo

Name: FISHING SPEAR
Description: A spearlike weapon with a barbed head used in hunting whales and large fish.

Name: LIQUOR
Description: Alcoholic beverage containing more than 20 percent alcohol.

Name: SPIDER
Description: Any predatory silk-producing arachnid of the order Araneae, having four pairs of legs and a rounded unsegmented body consisting of abdomen and cephalothorax.

Name: KIND (THING)
Description: A category of things distinguished by a common characteristic or quality.

Name: MURDER
Description: The intentional or premeditated killing of another person.

Name: TIGER
Description: A large carnivorous animal (Panthera tigris) of the cat family indigenous to Asia.

Name: THIRSTY
Description: Feeling the need to drink.

Name: THIRST
Description: A physiological need to drink.

Name: SPRING (OF WATER)
Description: A place where ground water flows naturally from a rock or the soil onto the land surface or into a body of surface water.

Name: SQUARE
Description: A geometrical figure with four sides that meet each other on right angles, or something resembling its shape.

Name: STABLE
Description: A building or structure usually with stalls that is used to house and feed horses, cattle or other animals.

Name: PRIEST
Description: A minister of the Catholic church empowered to administer the sacraments, most particularly that of the Eucharist or Holy Communion, as well as those of confession and extreme unction.

Name: ALTAR
Description: Table for religious ceremonies.

Name: KETTLE
Description: A metal container used to boil any kind of liquid.

Name: SEIZE
Description: To grasp and hold firmly.

Name: HIRE
Description: To employ a person or people in exchange of some kind of remuneration, usually a payment.

Name: STONE
Description: A general term for rock that is used in construction, either crushed for use as aggregate or cut into shaped blocks as dimension stone.

Name: STORM
Description: An atmospheric disturbance involving perturbations of the prevailing pressure and wind fields on scales ranging from tornadoes to extratropical cyclones; also the associated weather and the like. (Source: MGH)

Name: STOVE
Description: A chamber within which a fuel-air mixture is burned to provide heat, the heat itself being radiated outward from the chamber; used for space heating, process-fluid heating, and steel blast furnaces.

Name: CAUSE
Description: That which brings about any condition or produces any effect.

Name: JUDGE
Description: A person who decides the fate of someone or something that has been called into question.

Name: SUGAR
Description: A sweet crystalline or powdered substance, white when pure, consisting of sucrose obtained mainly from sugar cane and sugar beets and used in many foods, drinks, and medicines to improve their taste.

Name: EDGE
Description: The boundary of a surface.

Name: PUMPKIN
Description: A squash fruit of the Cucurbita genus, most commonly orange in colour when ripe and traditionally used during Halloween.

Name: FAME
Description: The state or quality of having a positive reputation.

Name: WIN
Description: To achieve a victory.

Name: GLOVE
Description: A garment for a hand, often extending to the wrist and sometimes up to the elbow, which either covers each finger individually, or separates the thumb from the other fingers.

Name: BANANA
Description: The fruit of the banana tree.

Name: BLADE
Description: The flat, sharp-edged part of a tool.

Name: BREATH
Description: The air inhaled and exhaled through the lungs.

Name: RATTLESNAKE
Description: Poisonous snake of the genus Crotalus, known by the rattling tail.

Name: TAR
Description: A viscous material composed of complex, high-molecular-weight, compounds derived from the distillation of petroleum or the destructive distillation of wood or coal.

Name: TAX
Description: An amount of money demanded by a government for its support or for specific facilities or services, most frequently levied upon income, property or sales.

Name: CANDY
Description: Food item that is rich in sugar.

Name: SHOEMAKER
Description: A person whose profession is making and repairing footwear.

Name: ARCH
Description: An arch-shaped arrangement of trapezoidal stones, designed to redistribute downward force outward.

Name: MASON
Description: A craftsman who builds in stone or brick otherwise known as masonry.

Name: HELL
Description: In various religions, the place where sinners are said to go after death.

Name: COUGH
Description: To force air from the lungs out the mouth, sometimes involuntarily, accompanied by a rough sound.

Name: REPEAT
Description: To do something again.

Name: TAILOR
Description: Someone who professionally manufactures clothing.

Name: PARROT
Description: Any bird of the order Psittaciformes, many species of which are colourful and able to mimic human speech.

Name: TERMITE
Description: A soft-bodied insect of the order Isoptera; individuals feed on cellulose and live in colonies with a caste system comprising three types of functional individuals: sterile workers and soldiers, and the reproductives.

Name: SHARE
Description: To give part of what one has to somebody else to use or consume.

Name: OPPOSITE
Description: The contrary; being opposed to something.

Name: PARAKEET
Description: Any of several slender species of parrot.

Name: BITTER
Description: Having an acrid taste.

Name: POISONOUS
Description: That acts like a poison.

Name: FLAME
Description: A bright yellow, red or bluish light which emerges during combustion processes.

Name: MULE
Description: The offspring of a male donkey and a female horse.

Name: TIDE
Description: The periodic rise and fall of the water resulting from gravitational interaction between the sun, moon and earth.

Name: TIME
Description: The dimension of the physical universe which, at a given place, orders the sequence of events.

Name: TIN (METAL)
Description: A metallic element with symbol Sn, occurring in cassiterite. It is a malleable silvery-white metal.

Name: TOAD
Description: Any anuran amphibian of the family Bufonidae, such as Bufo bufo of Europe. They are similar to frogs but are more terrestrial, having a drier warty skin.

Name: TORTOISE
Description: Any herbivorous terrestrial chelonian reptile of the family Testudinidae, of most warm regions, having a heavy dome-shaped shell and clawed limbs.

Name: ANACONDA (WATER BOA)
Description: Any of various large non-venomous snakes of the genus Eunectes, found mainly in northern South America.

Name: SWALLOW
Description: The reflex in the human body that makes something pass from the mouth to the pharynx and into the esophagus, with the shutting of the epiglottis.

Name: TRADE
Description: The act or the business of buying and selling for money. Mercantile or commercial business in general or the buying and selling, or exchanging, of commodities, either by wholesale or retail within a country or between countries. (Source: WESTS)

Name: PRESIDENT
Description: The title of one who presides over an organisation, company, trade union, university, country, etc.

Name: TRAIN
Description: A self-propelled, connected group of vehicles moving on rails.

Name: ADOBE
Description: An unburnt brick dried in the sun made of clay and dried grasses.

Name: ADULTERY
Description: Sex by a married person with someone other than their spouse.

Name: ASPEN
Description: A kind of poplar tree (genus Populus; section Populus).

Name: BERRY
Description: A soft fruit which develops from a superior ovary and contains seeds not encased in pits.

Name: BORING
Description: Causing boredom.

Name: TREE
Description: Any large woody perennial plant with a distinct trunk giving rise to branches or leaves at some distance from the ground.

Name: OLD WOMAN
Description: An old woman.

Name: DRUM
Description: A percussion instrument consisting of at least one membrane that is stretched over a shell and struck directly with the player's hands or with a drumstick.

Name: GARBAGE
Description: Unwanted or undesired material, usually discarded.

Name: DEATH
Description: The end of life.

Name: TEMPLE
Description: A house of worship and spiritual activities.

Name: COYOTE
Description: (Canis latrans) A member of the Canidae family native to North America.

Name: CROW
Description: A bird, usually black, of the genus Corvus, having a strong conical beak, with projecting bristles; it has a harsh, croaking call.

Name: SCULPTOR
Description: A person who practices the art of sculpture.

Name: SINK (BASIN)
Description: A bowl for washing hands, dishwashing or other purposes, often affixed to a wall.

Name: LINEN
Description: A material made from the fibers of the flax plant.

Name: ORNAMENT
Description: An element of decoration.

Name: INCLINATION
Description: A likelihood of behaving in a particular way or going in a particular direction.

Name: CHILI PEPPER
Description: Any fruit of a plant of the botanical genus Capsicum, noted for their spicy and burning flavour due to presence of capsaicin.

Name: GRAPE
Description: A small, round, smooth-skinned edible fruit, usually purple, red, or green, that grows in bunches on certain vines.

Name: VALLEY
Description: Any low-lying land bordered by higher ground; especially an elongate, relatively large, gently sloping depression of the Earth's surface, commonly situated between two mountains or between ranges of hills or mountains, and often containing a stream with an outlet.

Name: PEAR
Description: A fruit produced by the pear tree.

Name: LOVE
Description: To have an intense feeling of affection and care towards another person.

Name: VEGETABLES
Description: Any of various herbaceous plants having parts that are used as food.

Name: CASSAVA
Description: Shrub (Manihot esculenta) whose roots are rich in starch.

Name: RICE
Description: Seeds of the rice plant (Oryza sativa) used as food.

Name: MANIOC
Description: Shrub (Manihot esculenta) whose roots are rich in starch.

Name: EMBRACE
Description: To squeeze someone in one's arms.

Name: VERMIN
Description: Small animals and insects that can be harmful and which are difficult to control when they appear in large numbers. (Source: CAMB)

Name: VILLAGE
Description: A group of houses and other buildings, such as a church, a school and some shops, which is smaller than a town, usually in the countryside.

Name: MILLET
Description: A group of small-seeded species of cereal crops, widely grown around the world for food and fodder.

Name: BARLEY
Description: A strong cereal of the genus Hordeum, or its grains, often used as food or to make malted drinks.

Name: WALL (OF HOUSE)
Description: The outer structure which encloses a building.

Name: BUFFALO
Description: A wild heavy bison of the species Bison bison, having a broad massive horned head.

Name: WAR
Description: A conflict or a state of hostility between two or more parties, nations or states, in which armed forces or military operations are used.

Name: STALLION
Description: An uncastrated male horse.

Name: BIRD
Description: Any of the bipedal, warm-blooded vertebrates that lay eggs having wings which, for most species, enables them to fly.

Name: MARE
Description: An adult female horse.

Name: HORN (INSTRUMENT)
Description: A wind instrument made of a wound copper tube with a wide sound bucket and valves.

Name: STRAIN
Description: To separate or isolate components from a liquid with the help of a filter.

Name: MEAD
Description: Wine made of honey.

Name: HONEY
Description: A viscous, sweet substance produced from nectar or honeydew by bees.

Name: WATERFALL
Description: A perpendicular or steep descent of the water of a stream.

Name: SALMON
Description: One of several species of fish of the Salmonidae family.

Name: SPEAR
Description: a long, stabbing weapon for thrusting or throwing, consisting of a wooden shaft to which a sharp-pointed head, as of iron or steel, is attached.

Name: BLOOD
Description: A fluid connective tissue consisting of the plasma and cells that circulate in the blood vessels.

Name: STREAM
Description: A small river or large creek; a body of moving water confined by banks.

Name: WATER
Description: Common liquid (H₂O) which forms rain, rivers, the sea, etc., and which makes up a large part of the bodies of organisms.

Name: WATER LEECH
Description: A worm-like creature that lives in water and sucks blood from animals.

Name: SEAGULL
Description: A seabird of the genus Larus or of the family Laridae.

Name: WEAPONS
Description: An instrument of attack or defense in combat, as a gun, missile, or sword.

Name: WEATHER
Description: The day-to-day meteorological conditions, especially temperature, cloudiness, and rainfall, affecting a specific place.

Name: RAPE
Description: The act of forcing sexual intercourse or other sexual activity upon another person against their will.

Name: WELL
Description: A hole dug into the earth to reach a supply of water, oil, brine or gas.

Name: GREASY
Description: Smeared or soiled with grease or oil.

Name: FLEE
Description: Leaving a dangerous or unpleasant situation.

Name: WHALE
Description: Large marine mammals of the order Cetacea; the body is streamlined, the broad flat tail is used for propulsion, and the limbs are balancing structures.

Name: WILD ANIMAL
Description: A non-domesticated animal living independently of man.

Name: WAGON
Description: A wheeled vehicle, generally drawn by horse power.

Name: WIND
Description: The motion of air relative to the earth's surface; usually means horizontal air motion, as distinguished from vertical motion.

Name: PEBBLES
Description: Small stone abraded by water.

Name: WOMAN
Description: An adult human member of the sex that produces ova and bears young.

Name: BOOK
Description: A collection of leaves of paper, parchment or other material, usually bound or fastened together within covers, containing writing of any type or blank pages for future inscription.

Name: WOOL
Description: The soft, curly hair that forms the fleece of sheep, lamas and other animals and which is used to produce clothing.

Name: WORLD
Description: The Earth with all its inhabitants and all things upon it.

Name: BRAKE
Description: Decelerate using a mechanical device.

Name: YEAST
Description: Many species of unicellular fungi, most of which belong to the Ascomycetes and reproduce by budding. The genus Saccharomyces is used in brewing and winemaking because in low oxygen concentration it produces zymase, an enzyme system that breaks down sugars to alcohol and carbon dioxide. Saccharomyces is also used in bread-making. Some yeasts are used as a source of protein and of vitamins of the B group. (Source: ALL)

Name: ACORN
Description: Fruit of the oak tree.

Name: CIGARETTE
Description: A product manufactured out of cured and finely cut leaves, which are rolled or stuffed into a paper-wrapped cylinder for smoking.

Name: COCONUT
Description: The large hard-shelled oval nut with a fibrous husk of the cocos palm.

Name: MUST
Description: To be required to do something.

Name: BE ABLE
Description: To have the ability to do something.

Name: NOODLE
Description: A string or strip of pasta, especially as used in Chinese and Italian cookery.

Name: TOBACCO
Description: Leaves of certain varieties of the tobacco plant, cultivated and harvested to make cigarettes, cigars, snuff, for smoking in pipes or for chewing.

Name: SPINACH
Description: An important leaf vegetable, grown throughout the temperate regions of the world.

Name: WEAR
Description: Fix clothes on your body and carry them.

Name: ARROW
Description: Pointed projectile that is shot with a bow.

Name: WAVE
Description: A disturbance in an fluid medium.

Name: FARMER
Description: A person who works the land or who keeps livestock, especially on a farm.

Name: HEEL
Description: The part of the human foot on the backside where it becomes the leg.

Name: ELBOW
Description: The joint between arm and forearm.

Name: LIME (FRUIT)
Description: A green citrus fruit.

Name: CONVICT
Description: To find guilty of a crime as a result of legal proceedings.

Name: WORK (LABOUR)
Description: Productive activity, service, trade, or craft for which one is regularly paid.

Name: VINEGAR
Description: A sour liquid formed by the fermentation of alcohol with acetic acid bacteria used as a condiment or preservative.

Name: TOMATO
Description: The savoury fruit of the Solanum lycopersicum, red when ripe.

Name: REMAIN
Description: To continue to be in the same place or state.

Name: ACQUIT
Description: To pronounce not guilty of criminal charges.

Name: CLEAR
Description: Free of ambiguity or doubt.

Name: CREEK (TIDAL)
Description: A narrow inlet or bay, especially of the sea.

Name: FRY
Description: To cook in hot fat.

Name: CLIFF
Description: A steep coastal declivity which may or may not be precipitous, the slope angle being dependent partly on the jointing, bedding and hardness of the materials from which the cliff has been formed, and partly on the erosional processes at work.(Source: WHIT)

Name: RIVER BED
Description: The channel containing or formerly containing the water of a river.

Name: BOW
Description: A weapon made of a curved piece of wood or other flexible material whose ends are connected by a string, used for shooting arrows.

Name: QUIVER (FOR ARROWS)
Description: A container for arrows, crossbow bolts or darts, such as those fired from a bow, crossbow or blowgun.

Name: DEAF
Description: Not having the faculty of hearing, or only having a restricted capability to hear.

Name: BAOBAB TREE
Description: Genus of big trees (Adansonia) from the mallow family, growing in tropical countries.

Name: PUT
Description: To set or place an object somewhere.

Name: JOINT
Description: Any part of the body where two bones join.

Name: ANXIETY
Description: An unpleasant complex combination of emotions that includes fear, apprehension and worry, and is often accompanied by physical sensations such as palpitations, nausea, chest pain and/or shortness of breath.

Name: BLACKSMITH
Description: A craftsman expert in iron and other metals work.

Name: STATUE
Description: A three-dimension work of art, usually of a person or animal, usually created by sculpting, carving, moulding, or casting.

Name: PERMIT
Description: To give permission to an action.

Name: MUSCLE
Description: An organ formed by contractile tissue that moves other organs.

Name: TWINS
Description: A case of multiple birth in which the mother gives birth to two offspring from the same pregnancy.

Name: BRICK
Description: A building material usually made from clay, molded as a rectangular block, and baked or burned in a kiln.

Name: COW
Description: Female bovine animal (Bos taurus) of the subfamily Bovinae of the family Bovidae.

Name: BULL
Description: Male bovine animal.

Name: CHESTNUT TREE
Description: Any north temperate fagaceous tree of the genus Castanea, such as Castanea sativa, which produce flowers in long catkins and nuts in a prickly bur.

Name: BOUNDARY
Description: The dividing line or location between two areas.

Name: BRIDGE
Description: A structure that spans and provides a passage over a road, railway, river, or some other obstacle.

Name: LATCH
Description: A fastening for a door that has a bar that fits into a notch or slot, and is lifted by a lever or string from either side.

Name: FRESHWATER EEL
Description: A snake-like edible fish, which lives in freshwater.

Name: OR
Description: [Conjunction that indicates an alternative.]

Name: SOIL
Description: To make filthy.

Name: DRIZZLE
Description: Fine, light rain.

Name: APPEARANCE
Description: The outward or visible aspect of a person or thing.

Name: MEMORY
Description: The ability of an organism to record information combined with the facility of recall.

Name: RIGHT
Description: Something that is on the right side relative to another object.

Name: HANDKERCHIEF
Description: A piece of cloth, usually square and often fine and elegant, carried for wiping the face, nose or hands.

Name: TOWEL
Description: Piece of absorbent fabric or paper used for drying or wiping.

Name: BOOTY
Description: Profits from burglary, looting and raids.

Name: STUMP OF TREE
Description: The short piece left over after cutting off the most part.

Name: CHARACTER
Description: A symbol used to represent a sound or a word.

Name: WHISTLE
Description: To make a sound or a melody by forcing the breath out between closed lips.

Name: LOW TIDE
Description: the tide at the point of maximum ebb.

Name: BUG
Description: Any of the suborder Heteroptera, having piercing and sucking mouthparts, specialized as a beak. (Source: CED)

Name: YAWN
Description: To open the mouth widely and take a long, deep breath because of tiredness or boredom.

Name: JEWEL
Description: A precious stone such as a diamond, a sapphire or an agate.

Name: NECESSARY
Description: Needed for a purpose or a reason.

Name: ON PURPOSE
Description: (Doing or feeling something) in a deliberate or controlled way.

Name: CITIZEN
Description: A native or naturalized member of a state or nation who owes allegiance, bears responsibilities and obtains rights, including protection, from the government.

Name: GRIND
Description: To break something into small pieces by pressing it flat, or grinding it to powder.

Name: DEFENDANT
Description: Any party who is required to answer the complaint of a plaintiff in a civil lawsuit before a court.

Name: GOOD
Description: Having desired or positive qualities.

Name: OWNER
Description: One who owns.

Name: ELF
Description: A mythical creature of Germanic mythology. In Norse mythology they were originally minor gods of nature and fertility. They are often pictured as youthful-seeming men and women of great beauty living in forests and other natural places, underground, or in wells and springs. They have been portrayed to be long-lived or immortal and they have magical powers attributed to them.

Name: TEACHER
Description: A person who passes on knowledge, especially one employed in a school.

Name: SHOW
Description: To have somebody see something.

Name: HAIR
Description: The hair on humans, usually on the head but also including the hair on the body.

Name: INCREASE
Description: (Of a quantity) to become bigger.

Name: CARPENTER
Description: Artisan who works with wood.

Name: BRAID
Description: A hair style formed by interweaving three or more strands of hair.

Name: PILLOW
Description: Cushion placed under the head for sleeping.

Name: POET
Description: A person who writes poems.

Name: SHUT
Description: To move (a door, a window, etc.) so that it closes its opening.

Name: PURSUE
Description: Trying to achieve, to catch, or to reach something or someone.

Name: LINE
Description: An infinitely long, infinitely thin, not bent line in geometry.

Name: MOLAR TOOTH
Description: A tooth located in the back of the mouth used for crushing and grinding food.

Name: MOTHER-IN-LAW
Description: The mother of someone's spouse.

Name: CAN
Description: A small, round-shaped metal container, used for different purposes like storing food or liquids, or collecting money.

Name: LIGHT (WEIGHT)
Description: With a small mass, little weight or density; the opposite of heavy.

Name: HUNTER
Description: A person who hunts game.

Name: SMALLPOX
Description: A highly contagious viral disease characterized by fever and weakness and skin eruption with pustules that form scabs that slough off leaving scars.

Name: FATHER-IN-LAW
Description: The father of someone's spouse.

Name: SON-IN-LAW
Description: The male marital partner of someone's child.

Name: DAUGHTER-IN-LAW
Description: The female marital partner of someone's child.

Name: STEPDAUGHTER
Description: The daughter of one's spouse and his or her previous partner.

Name: STEPSON
Description: The son of one's spouse and his or her previous partner.

Name: CHILD-IN-LAW
Description: The spouse of someone's child.

Name: ARMOUR
Description: Clothing that soldiers wear to protect themselves during combat. Historically made of leather or metal, today special materials like kevlar are used.

Name: LAW
Description: A body of rules of action or conduct prescribed by a legislative authority, and having binding legal force.

Name: NEPHEW
Description: A son of someone's brother or sister.

Name: SHIELD
Description: A large plate made of metal or wood, held in the left hand during melee combat to protect the body from incoming attacks.

Name: SPIDER WEB
Description: A fine net of threads woven by a spider to catch insects.

Name: CRIME
Description: Any act done in violation of those duties which an individual owes to the community, and for the breach of which the law has provided that the offender shall make satisfaction to the public. (Source: BLACK)

Name: JUDGMENT
Description: The official and authentic decision of a court of justice upon the respective rights and claims of the parties to an action or suit therein litigated and submitted to its determination, the final decision of the court resolving the dispute and determining the rights and obligations of the parties.

Name: COURT
Description: An organ of the government, belonging to the judicial department, whose function is the application of the laws to controversies brought before it and the public administration of justice.

Name: GLUE
Description: Substance used for sticking objects together.

Name: BUS
Description: A large, long-bodied motor vehicle equipped with seating for passengers, usually operating as part of a scheduled service.

Name: HOOK
Description: A rod bent into a curved shape, for catching, holding, or sustaining anything.

Name: PRISONER
Description: A person confined in a prison, while on trial or serving a sentence.

Name: CAPTIVE
Description: A person held against his will.

Name: FISHHOOK
Description: A metal hook for catching fish.

Name: TRAP (PITFALL)
Description: A device for catching and holding animals.

Name: EMERGE (APPEAR)
Description: To become known or apparent.

Name: WHEAT
Description: Plant belonging to genus Triticum and to family Poaceae (also known as Gramineae).

Name: MAIN
Description: The most important element.

Name: FEEL
Description: To be in some emotional state.

Name: VULGAR
Description: Rude and likely to offend, using allusions on the sexual level.

Name: BILL
Description: Sum owed in a restaurant, or the relative bill.

Name: MERCHANT
Description: A businessperson engaged in trade.

Name: MESS
Description: A state of confusion and disorderliness.

Name: CALL
Description: To address or summon someone.

Name: FOLLOW
Description: To go or come after (in physical space) someone or something.

Name: WORK (ACTIVITY)
Description: To do a specific task by employing physical or mental powers.

Name: CONCEIVE
Description: To become pregnant.

Name: SINK (DESCEND)
Description: To go down in water, mud, quicksand etc. or to cause something to go down in it.

Name: FRAXINUS
Description: Any of the trees belonging to the genus Fraxinus.

Name: BE BORN
Description: To start living.

Name: SALTY
Description: Containing salt.

Name: HOPE
Description: To want something to happen or the belief in the possibility that something one wants will happen.

Name: MIDDLE
Description: What is equally far away from two ends or being in that position.

Name: FASTEN
Description: Tighten and close, for example a belt.

Name: LET GO OR SET FREE
Description: To give freedom; to stop holding; to release from confinement or restraint.

Name: SONG
Description: A musical piece with lyrics (or words to sing); prose that one can sing.

Name: ABANDON
Description: To give up control of, to surrender something.

Name: WEIGH
Description: To determine the weight of an object.

Name: RESIDE
Description: To have permanent residence.

Name: COOK (SOMETHING)
Description: To prepare a meal or a single dish.

Name: SUFFER
Description: To physically feel a damage, a pain, a disease or a punishment.

Name: CLIMB
Description: To mount to a high or little accessible place using feet and hands, e.g. a tree, a mountain or a ladder.

Name: SACRIFICE
Description: Something surrendered or lost in order to gain an objective.

Name: NURSE
Description: A person trained to provide care for the sick.

Name: CAMP
Description: Tents, cabins, etc., used as temporary lodgings by a group of travellers, holiday-makers, Scouts, Gypsies, etc.

Name: FALL ASLEEP
Description: To go to sleep; to change from waking state to sleeping state.

Name: GO OUT
Description: To move out of or depart from.

Name: UNCOVER
Description: To uncover; to show and display that which was hidden.

Name: WOUND
Description: A type of injury in which in skin or tisue is torn, cut,  punctured or otherwise hurt.

Name: SHARK
Description: A scaleless fish with a cartilaginous skeleton that has 5 to 7 gill slits on each side of its head.

Name: CAR
Description: A four-wheeled motor vehicle used for land transport, usually propelled by a gasoline or diesel internal combustion engine.

Name: SUCCEED
Description: To attain a desired goal.

Name: WRAP
Description: To surround on all sides.

Name: BULLET
Description: A projectile, usually of metal, shot from a gun at high speed.

Name: SPEECH
Description: An address or form of oral communication in which a speaker makes his thoughts and emotions known before an audience, often for a given purpose. (Source: RHW)

Name: DAMAGE
Description: To put a thing in bad condition by causing damage to it.

Name: LIKE
Description: To enjoy, be in favor/favour of.

Name: ACCUSTOM
Description: Get used to something.

Name: DIVIDE
Description: To split or separate something into two or more parts.

Name: HONEST
Description: Not disposed to cheat or defraud.

Name: SECRET
Description: Being or kept hidden from public perception.

Name: WAGES
Description: A fixed amount of money paid to a worker, usually measured on a monthly or annual basis.

Name: PREGNANT
Description: Carrying developing offspring within the body.

Name: PIPE
Description: A device consisting of a mouthpiece, a long pipe stem and a pipe bowl, that is used to smoke tobacco.

Name: BALD
Description: Without hair on the head.

Name: CITRUS FRUIT
Description: The fruits of a plant in the citrus genus. They have a leathery rind surrounding segments filled with pulp vesicles.

Name: SEND
Description: To make something (an object, a message) go from one place to another.

Name: ORDER
Description: To order someone or several persons by a superior authority to do something, or to arrange something in a tidy manner.

Name: PAINFUL
Description: Full of pain; causing uneasiness or distress, either physical or mental.

Name: WE (EXCLUSIVE)
Description: Exclusive we: I and at least one other person, but not the addressed person (you) (pronoun 1st person plural without 2nd person).

Name: WE (INCLUSIVE)
Description: Inclusive we: I and at least one other person, including the addressed person(s) (pronoun 1st person plural with 2nd person).

Name: BEAM
Description: A structural member loaded on its narrow face, and typically used in a horizontal or sloping position to span between bearing points.

Name: MATCH
Description: A stick with inflammable substance on one end that can be set on fire by friction.

Name: DIVORCE
Description: Legal dissolution of a marriage.

Name: KICK
Description: To strike somebody or something with the foot.

Name: RABBIT
Description: One of several small mammals of the family Leporidae, with long ears, long hind legs and a short, fluffy tail.

Name: TENDON
Description: Tissue that connects muscle to bone.

Name: FAIRY
Description: One of a class of female supernatural beings, generally conceived as having a diminutive human form and possessing magical powers.

Name: LEOPARD
Description: A large wild cat with a spotted coat, Panthera pardus, indigenous to Africa and Asia.

Name: FATIGUE
Description: A state of physical and/or mental weakness and a lack of vigor.

Name: PITY
Description: Deep awareness of the suffering of another, coupled with the wish to relieve it.

Name: URINE
Description: Liquid excrement consisting of water, salts and urea, which is made in the kidneys, stored in the bladder, then released through the urethra.

Name: OVEN
Description: An enclosed heated compartment usually lined with a refractory material used for baking or drying substances, firing ceramics, heat-treating, etc.

Name: WITNESS
Description: Someone who has a personal knowledge of something.

Name: SWAMP
Description: A permanently waterlogged area in which there is often associated tree growth, e.g. mangroves in hot climates.

Name: AUBERGINE
Description: An Asian plant, Solanum melongena, cultivated for its edible purple, green, or white ovoid fruit.

Name: PURE
Description: Free from contaminants or extraneous elements.

Name: BRUISE
Description: A collection of blood in the body tissue outside the blood vessels

Name: ORPHAN
Description: A person one or both of whose parents have died, especially a minor.

Name: THUNDER
Description: Sound produced by fast air expansion induced by a lightning.

Name: VEIL
Description: A head covering.

Name: BEGET
Description: (Especially of a male parent) to procreate or generate.

Name: CATTLE
Description: Domesticated bovine animals, including cows, steers and bulls, raised and bred on a ranch or farm.

Name: OLIVE
Description: The small oval fruit of the olive tree, Olea europaea.

Name: CAVE
Description: 1) An underground hollow with access from the ground surface or from the sea, often found in limestone areas and on rocky coastlines.2) A natural cavity, chamber or recess which leads beneath the surface of the earth, generally in a horizontal or obliquely inclined direction. It may be in the form of a passage or a gallery, its shape depending in part on the joint pattern or structure of the rock and partly on the type of process involved in its excavation. Thus, caves worn by subterranean rivers may be different in character from, and of considerably greater extent than, a sea-cave eroded by marine waves.3) A natural underground open space, generally with a connection to the surface and large enough for a person to enter. The most common type of cave is formed in a limestone by dissolution. (Source: CED /  WHIT /  BJGEO)

Name: OPEN
Description: To make the inside something accessible by moving an obstacle aside (e.g. a door or covering), or to move said obstacle.

Name: BECAUSE
Description: Conjunction initiating a causal phrase.

Name: STEP
Description: A flat surface or support that facilitates the ascent or descent of a stairway or step-ladder.

Name: FART
Description: To emit digestive gases through the anus.

Name: THIEF
Description: Someone who takes property belonging to someone else with the intention of keeping it or selling it.

Name: THREAD
Description: A long, thin and flexible form of material, generally with a round cross-section, used in sewing, weaving or in the construction of string.

Name: INTENTION
Description: An anticipated outcome that is intended to obtain or that guides your planned actions.

Name: BRIBE (AMOUNT)
Description: Something (usually money) given in exchange for influence or as an inducement to dishonesty.

Name: BRIBE (SOMEBODY)
Description: To give, or offer a bribe.

Name: MOUSTACHE
Description: A growth of facial hair between the nose and the upper lip.

Name: MOULD
Description: A frame or model around or on which something is formed or shaped.

Name: GRUEL
Description: A hot breakfast cereal dish made from oatmeal, milk and, or water heated and stirred until thick.

Name: HAWTHORN
Description: Any of various shrubs and small trees of the genus Crataegus having small, apple-like fruits and thorny branches.

Name: OX
Description: A castrated bull.

Name: TRAP (CATCH)
Description: To catch in a trap, to immobilize.

Name: MIRROR
Description: A smooth surface, usually made of glass with reflective material painted on the underside, that reflects light so as to give an image of what is in front of it.

Name: SHOOT
Description: To fire a shot from a firearm, bow or other weapon.

Name: EYEBROW
Description: The hair that grows over the bone ridge above the eye socket.

Name: YESTERDAY
Description: The day before today.

Name: GHOST
Description: The visible disembodied soul of a dead person.

Name: SPADE
Description: Tool having a flat and sharp metal tip and a wooden handle used to break, dig and move the earth.

Name: DIARRHEA
Description: A condition in which the sufferer has frequent and watery bowel movements.

Name: NOSTRIL
Description: Either of the two orifices located on the nose (or on the beak of a bird); used as a passage for air and other gases to travel the nasal passages.

Name: DAY AFTER TOMORROW
Description: On the day following tomorrow.

Name: DAY BEFORE YESTERDAY
Description: On the day before yesterday.

Name: PALM TREE
Description: Any of various evergreen trees from the family Palmae or Arecaceae, which are mainly found in the tropics.

Name: NOISE
Description: Sound which is unwanted, either because of its effects on humans, its effect on fatigue or malfunction of physical equipment, or its interference with the perception or detection of other sounds.

Name: PALM OF HAND
Description: The inner and somewhat concave part of the human hand that extends from the wrist to the bases of the fingers.

Name: DIMINISH
Description: To make smaller.

Name: VULTURE
Description: Any of several carrion-eating birds of the families Accipitridae and Cathartidae.

Name: LAST (ENDURE)
Description: To endure, continue over time.

Name: GOOSE
Description: Waterfowl of the Anatidae family.

Name: CHARCOAL
Description: A porous solid product containing 85-98% carbon and produced by heating carbonaceous materials such as cellulose, wood or peat at 500-600 C° in the absence of air. (Source: MGH)

Name: ULCER
Description: An open sore of the skin, eyes or mucous membrane, often caused by an initial abrasion and generally maintained by an inflammation and/or an infection.

Name: HARE
Description: Mammal of the family hares and rabbits (Leporidae) with long ears, short tail and hindlegs which are shorter than the forelegs and permit running quickly.

Name: COOKED RICE
Description: Boiled rice.

Name: THREATEN
Description: To make a threat of injury or punishment against someone.

Name: STEAM
Description: The gas phase of water.

Name: BEAVER
Description: A mammal of the genus Castor, having a wide, flat tail and webbed feet.

Name: GIVE BIRTH
Description: To release an offspring from one's own body; to cause to be born.

Name: PENALTY
Description: Punitive sanction taken against someone who has broken the law.

Name: BABOON
Description: Large ground based monkey having doglike muzzles.

Name: MANY
Description: An indefinite large number of.

Name: WIFE
Description: The female partner in a marriage.

Name: HUSBAND
Description: The male partner in a marriage.

Name: FEATHER
Description: A branching, hair-like structure that grows on the skin of birds and protects them against coldness and water and allows their wings to create lift.

Name: BIG
Description: Of a great size.

Name: LONG
Description: Having much distance from one terminating point on an object or an area to another terminating point.

Name: BARK
Description: The exterior covering of the trunk and branches of a tree.

Name: TONGUE
Description: The flexible muscular organ in the mouth that is used to move food around, for tasting and that is moved into various positions to modify the flow of air from the lungs in order to produce different sounds.

Name: BARKING
Description: To produce a loud, short, explosive sound similar to that of a dog.

Name: YOUNG
Description: In the early part of growth or life.

Name: CAT
Description: A common four-legged animal (Felis silvestris) that is often kept as a household pet.

Name: I
Description: The speaker or writer referring to himself or herself alone.

Name: HEAVY
Description: Of a physical object, having great weight.

Name: HE
Description: A male other; the male previously mentioned; himself.  3rd person singular masculine subject pronoun.

Name: WE
Description: The speaker or writer and at least one other person.

Name: YOU
Description: The group of persons addressed.

Name: THIS
Description: The indicated object, item, etc. close to the speaker.

Name: THOU
Description: The person addressed.

Name: MOTHER
Description: A woman who has at least one child.

Name: FATHER
Description: A male parent.

Name: ROPE
Description: Thick, strong string made of several strands that have been twisted together.

Name: WORM
Description: A generally tubular invertebrate of the annelid phylum.

Name: TAIL
Description: The appendage of an animal that is attached to its posterior and near the anus.

Name: NOSE
Description: The organ of the face used to breath and smell.

Name: PENIS
Description: The male sexual organ for copulation and urination; the tubular portion of the male genitalia (excluding the scrotum).

Name: HEART
Description: A muscular organ that pumps blood through the body.

Name: LIVER
Description: A large organ in the body that stores and metabolizes nutrients, destroys toxins and produces bile. Responsible for thousands of biochemical reactions.

Name: DAY (NOT NIGHT)
Description: The period between sunrise and sunset where one enjoys daylight.

Name: YEAR
Description: The time it takes the Earth to complete one revolution of the Sun (between 365.24 and 365.26 days depending on the point of reference).

Name: BOARD
Description: A piece of wood or similar material that has been sawn into a regular shape, usually in preparation for using it in some sort of construction.

Name: EARTH (SOIL)
Description: The soft and loose material forming a great part of the Earth surface.

Name: OLD
Description: Having lived or existed for a relatively long period of time.

Name: DIRTY
Description: Covered with or containing unpleasant substances such as dirt or grime.

Name: NEW
Description: Recently made, created or begun.

Name: WARM
Description: Having a temperature slightly higher than usual, still pleasant.

Name: NIGHT
Description: The period between sunset and sunrise, when a location faces far away from the sun, thus when the sky is dark.

Name: SMOOTH
Description: Not rough; having a surface texture that lacks friction.

Name: WHO
Description: What person or people; which person or people.

Name: WHAT
Description: Which thing.

Name: WHERE
Description: At what place?

Name: WHEN
Description: At what time?

Name: HOW
Description: In what way?

Name: NOT
Description: Negates the meaning of the modified verb or adjective.

Name: SOME
Description: An unspecified quantity or number of.

Name: FEW
Description: More than one, but not as many as usual or as expected.

Name: WIDE
Description: Having a long distance or area between two points, especially horizontally.

Name: THICK
Description: Relatively large distance from one surface to the opposite in its smallest solid dimension.

Name: BUTTER
Description: A soft, fatty foodstuff that is made by churning the cream of milk (most often cows milk).

Name: SMALL
Description: Not large or big; small in size.

Name: EAR
Description: The organ of hearing, consisting of the pinna, auditory canal, eardrum, malleus, incus, stapes and cochlea.

Name: EYE
Description: The organ that is sensitive to light, which it converts to electrical signals passed to the brain, by which means animals and humans see.

Name: SPIKE
Description: The fruiting body of a grain plant.

Name: JAGUAR
Description: A carnivorous spotted large cat native to South and Central America.

Name: BELLY
Description: The lower part of the front of the torso (or a comparable part of an animal), confined by the upper side by the midriff and the lowerside by the pelvis. Contains the intestines.

Name: HOUSE
Description: The abode of a human being, their place of residence.

Name: RAIN (RAINING)
Description: To fall from the clouds in drops of water.

Name: HANDLE
Description: A part of an object meant to hold that object with (e.g. the handle of a mug, pan or bag).

Name: SNOWING
Description: To fall from the clouds in the form of ice crystals.

Name: HEAD
Description: The part of the body of an animal or human which contains the brain, mouth and main sense organs.

Name: WING
Description: The appendage of an animal's (bird, bat, insect) body that enables it to fly in the air.

Name: FINGERNAIL
Description: The hard, flat, translucent covering near the tip of a human finger, useful for scratching and fine manipulation.

Name: WEDDING
Description: A ceremony celebrating the beginning of a marriage, during which the marrying parties exchanges vows.

Name: DAY (24 HOURS)
Description: A period of time lasting 24 hours.

Name: SING
Description: To produce harmonious sounds with one's voice.

Name: BROTHER
Description: A male person who has the same parents as another person.

Name: SISTER
Description: A female person who has the same parents as another person.

Name: CHANGE
Description: To make different or to become different.

Name: HIGH
Description: Being in a position comparatively far above to the ground.

Name: BRIDE
Description: A woman who is going to get married or has just got married.

Name: NARROW
Description: (Of a path, cave etc.) having a small width.

Name: YES
Description: A word used to show agreement or affirmation of something.

Name: NO
Description: A word used to show disagreement of something.

Name: WHY
Description: For what reason.

Name: DELIGHT
Description: To give pleasure to; to make happy or satisfied.

Name: AUNT
Description: A woman with one or more siblings who have one or more children; a sister of someone's father or mother.

Name: CANDLE
Description: A light source consisting of a wick embedded in a solid, flammable substance such as wax, tallow, or paraffin.

Name: SALT
Description: A condiment (NaCl - Sodium Chloride) used to add to or enhance the flavour of food (commonly with pepper).

Name: ANSWER
Description: To communicate a message of any form in reaction to something that has been asked or expressed, to the being who expressed it; to react verbally.

Name: AUTUMN
Description: The season after summer and before winter, traditionally from September 21 to December 20 in the northern hemisphere and from March 21 to June 20 in the southern hemisphere.

Name: HAND
Description: That part of the fore limb below the forearm or wrist in primates (including humans).

Name: VOMIT
Description: To regurgitate the contents of the stomach.

Name: FAT (OBESE)
Description: Carrying a larger-than-normal amount of fat or weight.

Name: FALL
Description: To descend in free fall due to the effect of gravity.

Name: PRISON
Description: A place in which individual persons have restricted personal freedom.

Name: FAT (FROM ANIMALS)
Description: The semisolid substance from animals which is used for cooking and as food.

Name: TODAY
Description: On the current day or date.

Name: BANK
Description: A financial institution where one can borrow money (upon which interest is due) or deposit money (in order to collect interest).

Name: IMPORTANT
Description: Having relevant and crucial value.

Name: HOT
Description: Having a very high temperature.

Name: COLD
Description: Having a low temperature.

Name: CAP
Description: A usually soft and close-fitting head covering, either having no brim or with a visor.

Name: BABY
Description: A very young human being, from birth to a year old.

Name: ELEPHANT
Description: A mammal of the order Proboscidea, having a trunk, and two large ivory tusks jutting from the upper jaw. Elephants are the largest land animals now existing.

Name: BACK
Description: The rear of body, especially the part between the neck and the end of the spine and opposite the chest and belly.

Name: BAD
Description: Not good; unfavorable; negative.

Name: MISTAKE
Description: A mistake, an oversight, a slight; usually apologetic, referring to one's own failures.

Name: ZERO
Description: The integer zero (0).

Name: STICK
Description: A long, thin piece of wood, mainly left in the shape in which it grew, that does not bend.
