Name: WALKING STICK
Description: An object, specifically for providing support when walking.

Name: LEG
Description: The limb of an animal (including humans) that extends from the groin to the ankle.

Name: NEWSPAPER
Description: A publication (usually published daily or weekly and printed on cheap, low-quality paper) that contains news and other articles.

Name: COFFEE
Description: A beverage made by infusing the beans of the coffee plant in hot water.

Name: COUNTRY
Description: A political entity asserting authority over a geographical area, or the area itself. Can be same as or part of a state.

Name: FOOT
Description: The part of a human’s body below the ankle that is used in order to stand and walk.

Name: FORK
Description: A utensil with spikes used to put solid food into the mouth.

Name: FINGER
Description: One of the long extremities of the hand that is used for gripping objects.

Name: CHILD (YOUNG HUMAN)
Description: A person below the age of puberty.

Name: CHIMNEY
Description: A vertical structure of brick, masonry, or steel that carries smoke or steam away from a fire, engine, etc.

Name: QUEEN
Description: A female monarch.

Name: LANGUAGE
Description: A system of communication using the spoken or signed word or using symbols that represent words, signs or sounds.

Name: DOUBT
Description: Uncertainty about the truth or accuracy of a matter.

Name: ASK (INQUIRE)
Description: To ask (a question) to somebody; to seek an answer to.

Name: CLEVER
Description: Mentally agile.

Name: VERY
Description: To a high or large degree.

Name: FOX
Description: A carnivorous relatively small canine of the species Vulpes Vulpes.

Name: MOON
Description: A natural satellite of a planet.

Name: QUIET
Description: With little or no sound; denoting absence of disturbing noise.

Name: RADIO
Description: A device that can capture the signal sent over radio waves and render the modulated signal as sound.

Name: TENT
Description: A portable lodging (usually made from waterproof plastic, animal hide or canvas streched by poles) that is used for sheltering people and objects from the weather when camping or at festivals.

Name: RAISE
Description: To cause to rise; to move something from a lower position to a higher one.

Name: CHICKEN
Description: A type of domesticated bird from the order of Galliformes which is often raised as a type of poultry (Gallus gallus domesticus).

Name: COWARD
Description: A person who lacks courage.

Name: APPLE
Description: The popular, crisp, round fruit of the apple tree, usually with red, yellow or green skin, light-coloured flesh and pips inside.

Name: BOTTLE
Description: A container, typically made of glass and having a tapered neck, used for holding liquids.

Name: BREAKFAST
Description: The first meal of the day, usually eaten in the morning.

Name: CLOCK
Description: An instrument used to measure or keep track of time.

Name: SLIP
Description: To fall over (usually unexpectedly) onto the ground or floor, due to the floor being slippery, smooth or slimy.

Name: FRIEND
Description: A person other than a family member, spouse or lover whose company one enjoys and towards whom one feels affection.

Name: DOWN
Description: Moving to a lower position.

Name: UNCLE
Description: The brother of someone’s father or mother.

Name: SCISSORS
Description: A tool used for cutting thin material, consisting of two crossing blades attached at a pivot point in such a way that the blades slide across each other when the handles are closed.

Name: TOMORROW
Description: The day after the present day.

Name: DEFEND
Description: To keep something or someone safe or prevent harm coming to someone or something.

Name: SHEEP
Description: A common, four-legged animal (Ovis) that is commonly kept by humans for its wool.

Name: NEIGHBOUR
Description: A person living in a house that is adjacent or nearby another person's house.

Name: NECK
Description: The part of the body (found in some animals, including humans) that connects the head and the trunk.

Name: GUTS
Description: The internal organs of an animal or human.

Name: WHITE
Description: Bright and colourless; reflecting equal quantities of all frequencies of visible light.

Name: EAT
Description: To consume something solid or semi-solid (usually food) by putting it into the mouth and eventually swallowing it.

Name: PIG
Description: A common, four-legged animal (Sus scrofa) that has cloven hooves, bristles and a nose adapted for digging and is farmed by humans for its meat.

Name: PEACE
Description: A state free of war, in particular war between different countries.

Name: MORNING
Description: The period of time from the start of the day (midnight) until midday (12:00).

Name: WITH
Description: In the company of.

Name: HEAT UP
Description: To cause an increase in temperature of an object or space; to cause something to become hot.

Name: SUMMER
Description: Traditionally the second of the four seasons regarded as being from June 21 to September 20 (or just June, July and August) in the Northern Hemisphere and from December 21 to March 20 (or just December, January and February) in the Southern Hemisphere.

Name: SUN
Description: The particular star at the centre of our solar system, from which the Earth gets light and heat.

Name: RAM
Description: A male sheep.

Name: EWE
Description: A female sheep.

Name: THROAT
Description: The front part of the neck.

Name: NAPE (OF NECK)
Description: The back part of the neck.

Name: BOAR (MALE PIG)
Description: An adult male pig.

Name: CHURCH
Description: A building where Christian religious activities take place.

Name: MONKEY
Description: A primate from the group *New World monkeys* or *Old World monkeys* (Simiiformes, excluding the superfamily Hominoidea or apes) that lives mainly in rainforests and is distinguished from an Ape by its smaller size and its tail.

Name: SOW (FEMALE PIG)
Description: An adult female pig.

Name: KNIFE
Description: A utensil consisting of a sharpened piece of hard material such as steel or other metal, ceramic, glass or stone, usually attached to a handle, that is formed in a manner that allows for cutting softer materials, especially meat or other food.

Name: HOUR
Description: A time period of sixty minutes; one twenty-fourth of a day.

Name: NEXT
Description: Following in a sequence.

Name: LAUGH
Description: To express pleasure, mirth or derision by peculiar movement of the muscles of the face, particularly of the mouth, causing a lighting up of the face and eyes, and usually accompanied by the emission of explosive or chuckling sounds from the chest and throat.

Name: NUMBER
Description: An abstract entity used to describe quantity.

Name: DAUGHTER
Description: An animal's female offspring (including that of a human).

Name: ENEMY
Description: Someone who is hostile to, feels hatred towards, opposes the interests of, or intends injury to someone else.

Name: SEPARATE
Description: To cause something or someone to move away from something or someone else.

Name: DUCK
Description: An aquatic bird of the family Anatidae, having a flat bill and webbed feet.

Name: TOOL
Description: A mechanical device intended to make a task easier.

Name: STREET
Description: A paved part of road, usually in a village or a town.

Name: VOICE
Description: The sound and tones human beings are able to produce with the vocal cords.

Name: HEALTHY
Description: In good physical and mental condition; free from disease.

Name: KITCHEN
Description: A room equipped for preparing and cooking food.

Name: BOY
Description: A young male person, usually a child or teenager.

Name: CROSS
Description: A geometrical figure consisting of two straight lines or bars bisecting each other, or any figure or object of similar shape.

Name: BREAD
Description: A common food made mainly from flour, water and yeast and produced by kneading and baking a dough.

Name: GOLD
Description: A heavy yellow elemental metal of great value, with atomic number 79 and symbol Au.

Name: MONTH
Description: A period into which a year is divided, historically based on the phases of the moon. In the Gregorian calendar there are twelve months.

Name: KNEE
Description: In man, the joint in the middle part of the leg.

Name: MEDICINE
Description: A substance which specifically promotes healing.

Name: TEA
Description: The drink made by infusing dried leaves or buds in hot water.

Name: RING
Description: A round piece of (precious) metal worn around the finger.

Name: WINDOW
Description: An opening, usually covered by one or more panes of clear glass, to allow light from outside to enter a building or vehicle.

Name: NOW
Description: At present; at this time.

Name: VISIT
Description: To go and see a person or place.

Name: SPOON
Description: An implement for eating or serving, a small bowl with a long straight handle.

Name: TELEPHONE
Description: An electronic device used for calling people.

Name: TOOTH
Description: A hard, calcareous structure present in the mouth of many vertebrate animals (including humans), generally used for eating.

Name: SHOE
Description: A protective covering for the foot, with a bottom part composed of thick leather or plastic sole and often a thicker heel, and a softer upper part made of leather or synthetic material. Shoes generally do not extend above the ankle, as opposed to boots, which do.

Name: NEEDLE (FOR SEWING)
Description: A thin, sharp implement used in sewing, knitting and acupuncture.

Name: GRANDFATHER
Description: The father of one of someone's parents.

Name: SECOND
Description: That which comes after the first.

Name: PEPPER
Description: A spice prepared from the fermented, dried, unripe red berries of the pepper plant.

Name: LION
Description: A large cat (Panthera leo) that is native to Africa, Asia and formerly much of Europe.

Name: ARRIVE
Description: To come to a destination.

Name: SHADE
Description: Darkness, where light (particularly sunlight) is blocked.

Name: TOE
Description: One of the extremities of the foot.

Name: WRONG
Description: Not correct.

Name: TOWN
Description: An area with residential districts, shops and amenities, and its own local government.

Name: LOUSE
Description: A small wingless parasitic insect of the order Phthiraptera that lives on humans, other mammals and birds.

Name: HORN (ANATOMY)
Description: A hard growth of keratin that protrudes from the top of the head of certain animals.

Name: BONE
Description: Any of the components of an endoskeleton, consisting mainly of calcium phosphate, collagen and cells.

Name: ROUND
Description: Circular or having a circular cross-section in at least one direction.

Name: SHARP
Description: Having the ability to cut easily.

Name: DULL
Description: Lacking the ability to cut easily; not sharp.

Name: DRY
Description: (Almost) free from liquid or moisture.

Name: CLAY
Description: A loose, earthy, extremely fine-grained, natural sediment or soft rock composed primarily of clay-size or colloidal particles and characterized by high plasticity and by a considerable content of clay mineral and subordinate amounts of finely divided quartz, decomposed feldspar, carbonates, ferruginous matter, and other impurities; it forms a plastic, moldable mass when finely ground and mixed with water, retains its shape on drying, and becomes firm, rocklike and permanently hard on heating or firing.

Name: THIN (SLIM)
Description: Carrying little fat (of people).

Name: DRINK
Description: To consume a liquid through the mouth.

Name: BREAST
Description: The fleshy organ on the chest of a sexually mature human female containing mammary glands.

Name: BITE
Description: Clamping the teeth hard on something.

Name: STRAIGHT
Description: Not crooked or bent; having a constant direction throughout its length.

Name: NAME
Description: Any word or phrase which designates a particular person, place, class or thing.

Name: FAR
Description: Having a large intervening distance with regard to something.

Name: BREATHE
Description: To repeatedly draw air into, and expel it from, the lungs, in order to extract oxygen from it and excrete waste products.

Name: HEAR
Description: To perceive sound with the ear, without necessarily paying attention to it.

Name: SEE
Description: To perceive [images] with the eye, without necessarily paying attention to them.

Name: KNOW (SOMETHING)
Description: To be sure about something or be acquainted with something.

Name: LIE (REST)
Description: To rest in a horizontal, static position, usually on another surface.

Name: RUDE
Description: Bad mannered.

Name: PLAY
Description: To act in a manner such that one has fun; to engage in playful activities expressly for the purpose of recreation.

Name: SQUEEZE
Description: To apply pressure to something from two or more sides at once.

Name: THINK (REFLECT)
Description: To actively and consciously use one's mental powers, usually to form ideas.

Name: SIT
Description: To be in a position with the upper body upright and the legs resting.

Name: KILL
Description: To put to death; to end a life.

Name: DIG
Description: To move earth, rocks, etc. out of the way, usually to create a hole.

Name: FEAR (BE AFRAID)
Description: To be scared of; to have an uncontrollable emotion of anxiety about something that causes a scared reaction or frightening impression.

Name: COUNT
Description: To determine the amount of something or to enumerate the digits of one's numeral system.

Name: SUCK
Description: To draw in a substance by creating a practical vacuum in the mouth, and as a result a difference in pressure.

Name: BE ALIVE
Description: To be alive; to have a life.

Name: FIGHT
Description: To be involved in a physical confrontation.

Name: YELLOW
Description: Having the colour of a yolk, a lemon or gold.

Name: GREEN
Description: Having green as its colour; having the hue of that portion of the visible spectrum lying between yellow and blue, evoked in the human observer by radiant energy with wavelengths of approximately 490 to 570 nanometers.

Name: EXPENSIVE
Description: Having a high price, cost.

Name: BEAUTIFUL
Description: Having nice or positive properties (specifically with regard to the senses, and most commonly, that of sight).

Name: BURNING
Description: To be consumed by fire.

Name: FULL
Description: Containing the most or maximum amount possible in the given available space.

Name: STAR
Description: A luminous celestial body that is made from gases (particularly hydrogen and helium) and forms the shape of a sphere.

Name: FREEZE
Description: To reach a chemically solid state, by the process of cooling.

Name: CUT
Description: To perform an incision (for example, with a knife).

Name: HIT
Description: To hit against with a sharp blow or to impel, usually with a hand or weapon or to be forcefully or suddenly contacting, e.g. a tree falling down and hitting the ground.

Name: STAB
Description: To perforate the surface of something with a pointed tool or weapon.

Name: HUNT
Description: To chase down prey and (usually) kill it.

Name: SCRATCH
Description: To rub or scrape (a part of the body) with a sharp object (e.g. to relieve an itching).

Name: SPLIT
Description: To divide fully or partly along a more or less straight line.

Name: FOOL
Description: A person with poor judgment or little intelligence.

Name: SWIM
Description: To move through the water, without touching the bottom.

Name: SPIT
Description: To forcefully evacuate saliva from the mouth.

Name: FLY (MOVE THROUGH AIR)
Description: To move autonomously through the air, without any part of the object or object's enclosure touching anything attached to the ground.

Name: STAND
Description: To be upright in an erect position, supported by the feet.

Name: WALK
Description: To move from one place to another by moving legs alternately, so that at least one foot is in contact with the floor or surface at any one time.

Name: TURN AROUND
Description: Change the direction in which one is moving or facing.

Name: TURN (SOMETHING)
Description: To position by moving an object around its axis.

Name: COME
Description: To move toward or to reach either the speaker, the person spoken to, or the subject of the speaker's narrative.

Name: GIVE
Description: To transfer the possession or holding (of an object) to another person.

Name: HOLD
Description: To grasp or grip (particularly with the hand) so that the object does not end up at the surface below.

Name: RUB
Description: To move one's hand or an object over a surface or other object (maintaining constant contact and applying moderate pressure).

Name: ROOM
Description: A separate part of a building, enclosed by walls, a floor and a ceiling.

Name: SMILE
Description: To make an upwards movement of the sides of the mouth, that indicates happiness or satisfaction.

Name: PUSH
Description: To apply a force to (an object), in order that it moves away from the origin of the force that was applied.

Name: WASH
Description: To remove dirt and grime from an object, using water (usually with soap).

Name: WIPE
Description: To move an object or utensil over a surface or other object while maintaining contact, in order that a substance be removed from its surface.

Name: SKELETON

Name: ACROSS

Name: PENIS SHEATH

Name: ORAL CAVITY

Name: FIRE OR FIREWOOD

Name: TWO HUNDRED

Name: SPEARTHROWER

Name: HAIR OR FUR

Name: BLOW (WITH NOSE)

Name: MACHETE

Name: LUTE

Name: AUNT OR UNCLE

Name: EAGLE OR HAWK

Name: CAPRINE (GOAT OR SHEEP)

Name: CARP (FISH)

Name: CRUSTACEANS (PRAWNS OR SHRIMP)

Name: STEELYARD (BALANCE)

Name: FOOT (UNIT)

Name: LADDER OR STAIRS

Name: PATERNAL AUNT (FATHER'S SISTER)

Name: BROTHER-IN-LAW (YOUNGER SISTER'S HUSBAND)

Name: BROTHER-IN-LAW (HUSBAND'S OLDER BROTHER)
Description: Husband of one's older brother.

Name: BROTHER-IN-LAW (HUSBAND'S YOUNGER BROTHER)
Description: Husband of one's younger brother.

Name: SISTER-IN-LAW (HUSBAND'S OLDER SISTER)
Description: Husband of one's older sister.

Name: SISTER-IN-LAW (HUSBAND'S YOUNGER SISTER)

Name: GRANDSON (SON'S SON)

Name: GRANDCHILD (DAUGHTER'S OFFSPRING)

Name: FADE (LOOSE COLOR)

Name: INHALE

Name: GNAW

Name: CLOG (SOMETHING)

Name: TALK

Name: FLATTER
Description: To praise somebody openly.

Name: TAKE A PHOTO
Description: To make a photography.

Name: TRANSPORT

Name: GET DIZZY

Name: HAVE A FEVER
Description: Have an increased body temperature.

Name: HAVE DIARRHEA

Name: DESPISE

Name: BLAME (SOMEBODY)

Name: STEEP

Name: STRONG (OF DRINK)

Name: FAT (OILY)

Name: TREE (CLASSIFIER)

Name: TUFT (CLASSIFIER)

Name: BUD (CLASSIFIER)

Name: BOTTLE (CLASSIFIER)

Name: MOUTHFUL (CLASSIFIER)

Name: SHEET (CLASSIFIER)

Name: HAT (CLASSIFIER)

Name: NEEDLE (CLASSIFIER)

Name: HOUSE (CLASSIFIER)

Name: BRIDGE (CLASSIFIER)

Name: DOOR (CLASSIFIER)

Name: CAR (CLASSIFIER)

Name: SHIP (CLASSIFIER)
Description: Classifier for ships.

Name: AFFAIR (CLASSIFIER)

Name: DEAL (CLASSIFIER)

Name: WALK (CLASSIFIER)
Description: Classifier for walks (strolls).

Name: BEAT (CLASSIFIER)

Name: BIT (CLASSIFIER)
Description: Classifier for classifier for small units of time.

Name: SUNNY DAY
Description: A day full of sunshine.

Name: CLOUDY DAY
Description: A day with many clouds.

Name: PLUM BLOSSOM
Description: The flower of the Chinese Plum.

Name: APRICOT BLOSSOM
Description: The flower of the Apricot Tree.

Name: PEACH BLOSSOM
Description: The flower of the Peach Tree.

Name: OSMANTHUS FRAGRANS
Description: A small tree species native to Asia from the Himalayas through southern China.

Name: SWEET OLIVE FLOWER
Description: The flower of teh Osmanthus Fragrans.

Name: UNHUSKED RICE
Description: The unhusked crops of the rice plant.

Name: GLUTINOUS RICE
Description: A type of rice grown mainly in Southeast and East Asia and the eastern parts of South Asia, which has opaque grains, very low amylose content, and is especially sticky when cooked. Also called oryza sativa var. glutinosa, sticky rice, sweet rice or waxy rice.

Name: BY (PASSIVE MARKER)
Description: Marker of the agent in a passive sentence.

Name: UNTIL
Description: Up to that point in time.

Name: TOWARDS
Description: Going into the direction of.

Name: BUSY
Description: The state of being occupied with something.

Name: IDLE
Description: The state of not being occupied with anything.

Name: ANGULAR (SQUAREFORMED)
Description: Having the form of a square.

Name: CAREFUL
Description: Be cautious.

Name: RECOMMEND

Name: MAKE A JOKE

Name: BEND (ONESELF)

Name: BLOCK (THE WAY)

Name: CHERRY

Name: MEAT DISHES

Name: LITCHI

Name: PORK

Name: JACKET

Name: SHAWL

Name: KITCHEN KNIFE

Name: FINGERTIP

Name: LITTLE FINGER

Name: FORENOON

Name: WILD GOOSE

Name: PIG TONGUE

Name: PIG LIVER

Name: CHICKEN EGG

Name: FOOT (MEASURE)

Name: SCALES (MEASURE INSTRUMENT)

Name: CRUCIAN CARP

Name: BIVALVIA (MUSSELS OR OYSTERS)

Name: CONSUME (DRINK OR EAT)

Name: LADLE (WATER)
Description: To use some device or one's hands to fill fluid from one container to another.

Name: BURP

Name: HIGH OR TALL
Description: Being in a position comparatively far above to the ground or be of great height (of objects and persons).

Name: THIS MONTH
Description: The same month as today.

Name: LAST MONTH
Description: The month before this month.

Name: NEXT MONTH
Description: The month after this month.

Name: FIELD (UPLAND)

Name: MOSQUITO NET

Name: FISHING (WITH A HOOK)

Name: SESAME

Name: RIVER OR WATER

Name: LANGUAGE OR WORD
Description: A system of communication using the spoken or signed word or using symbols that represent words, signs or sounds or a distinct unit of language (sounds in speech or written letters) with a particular meaning, composed of one or more morphemes, and also of one or more phonemes that determine its sound pattern.

Name: FEMALE PERSON OR MOTHER
Description: A human belonging to the female sex or a woman who has at least one child.

Name: TOMORROW OR YESTERDAY
Description: The day after the present day or the day before today.

Name: SAGO GRUB
Description: A type of snout beetle of species Rhynchophorus ferrugineus commonly known as red palm weevil, Asian palm weevil or sago palm weevil.

Name: LEAF SPINE
Description: A hard, rigid extension of leaves with sharp, stiff ends.

Name: AMULET
Description: An object whose most important characteristic is the power ascribed to it to protect its owner from danger or harm.

Name: BIRTH (ACCOUCHEMENT)
Description: The process of giving birth to a child.

Name: BLACK MAN

Name: BLACK WOMAN
Description: Term used to describe women who are perceived to be dark-skinned.

Name: BLACKEN
Description: To change the color of something into black.

Name: BLUEBERRY

Name: BREASTBONE

Name: BUSHFIRE

Name: CRAB CLAW

Name: CRAYFISH (FRESHWATER)

Name: CUTTLEFISH

Name: DIALECT

Name: ECHO

Name: EMU

Name: FORD (CROSSING)

Name: GRASSLAND

Name: HIP BONE

Name: JEALOUS

Name: KANGAROO RAT

Name: KANGAROO SKIN
Description: The skin of a kangaroo.

Name: KNUCKLE

Name: LEFT HANDED

Name: LIE (FALSEHOOD)

Name: MOTH

Name: OYSTERS

Name: PENGUIN

Name: PYRE

Name: RUM

Name: SCROTUM

Name: SHOOTING STAR

Name: STARLIGHT

Name: SWAN

Name: TAME

Name: WHITE WOMAN
Description: Term used to describe women who are perceived to be light-skinned.

Name: TURMERIC

Name: CAULIFLOWER

Name: YOU (FORMAL ADDRESS)

Name: SIZE (OF OBJECT)

Name: MARCH

Name: APRIL

Name: OCTOBER

Name: NOVEMBER

Name: DECEMBER
Description: The 12th month of the Gregorian calendar.

Name: CHANGE (SOMETHING)

Name: CHANGE (BECOME DIFFERENT)
Description: To be modified.

Name: STREAM (FLOW CONTINUOUSLY)

Name: SMOKE (EMIT SMOKE)

Name: BOLT (MOVE IN HASTE)

Name: BUDGE (ONESELF)

Name: CONNECT

Name: DASH (OF VEHICLE)

Name: DECREASE
Description: To become smaller in number or size.

Name: DIE (FROM ACCIDENT)
Description: To cease to live due to unforeseen circumstances.

Name: DROP (SOMETHING)
Description: To let something fall down.

Name: CALCULATE
Description: To determine by mathematical processes.

Name: DRIVE (CATTLE)
Description: Cause animals to move while following them.

Name: BOTHER (HARASS)
Description: To annoy persistently.

Name: RECOGNIZE (SOMEBODY)
Description: Perceive to see something or someone previously known.

Name: SWING (MOVEMENT)
Description: To move freely to and fro.

Name: IMPROVE (SOMETHING)
Description: Improvement is the process of a thing moving from one state to a state considered to be better, usually through some action intended to bring about that better state.

Name: MOVE (AFFECT EMOTIONALLY)
Description: To affect somebody emotionally.

Name: MOVE (ONESELF)
Description: To get oneself in motion in order to arrive at some other place.

Name: RING (MAKE SOUND)
Description: Ring most broadly refers to a hollow circular shape or to a high-pitched sound.

Name: ROAR (OF SEA)
Description: A sound emitted by a stormy sea.

Name: RUSTLE (OF LEAVES)
Description: A sound emitted by leaves moving in the trees.

Name: SEAT (SOMEBODY)
Description: To cause somebody to sit (e.g. by offering a seat).

Name: SOUND (OF INSTRUMENT OR VOICE)
Description: The noise emitted by musical instruments or humans speaking.

Name: HALT (STOP)
Description: To halt one’s movement.

Name: URGE (SOMEONE)
Description: To encourage someone to do something.

Name: ADD
Description: Join or unite so as to bring about an increase.

Name: DISTURB
Description: Interfere with somebody.

Name: HANG
Description: Remain suspended to some point above.

Name: HERD (SOMETHING)
Description: Keep or move animals together.

Name: PRODUCE
Description: To cause to have existence.

Name: THAW (DEW)
Description: Go from a frozen to a liquid state.

Name: TINKLE
Description: Emit a sound suggestive of a tinkle.

Name: TWINKLE
Description: Shine with flickering light.

Name: WALK (TAKE A WALK)
Description: To wander around.

Name: TIE UP (TETHER)
Description: To attach an animal to something to prevent that it leaves.

Name: MAKE ANGRY (ANNOY)
Description: To cause somebody to be annoyed.

Name: NOTICE (SOMETHING)
Description: To become aware of something.

Name: TUMBLE (FALL DOWN)
Description: To fall down accidentally.

Name: MAKE NOISE
Description: To be loud.

Name: CAUSE TO (LET)

Name: CHIME (ACTION)
Description: To ring the bells.

Name: CONVEY (A MESSAGE)
Description: To share a message with somebody.

Name: JOG (SOMETHING)

Description: To prevent something or somebody from being harmed.

Name: SWING (SOMETHING)
Description: To set something in swinging motion.

Name: BRAWL (FIGHT)
Description: To be involved in a normally unarmed and ruleless scuffle.

Name: CHAT (WITH SOMEBODY)
Description: To have a conversation with somebody.

Name: RINSE

Name: KNIT

Name: TRANSLATE
Description: To communicate of the meaning of a source-language text by means of an equivalent target-language text.

Name: ROT

Name: GUEST OR STRANGER
Description: Either a guest or a stranger.

Name: PREPARE
Description: To carry out things in advance to avoid to be later not able to do them.

Name: BACK (DIRECTION)
Description: The opposite direction from where one came.

Name: BACKWARD
Description: Moving in the direction of one's backside.

Name: FORWARD
Description: Moving ahead.

Name: ONCE (IN THE PAST)
Description: One time during a certain time in the past.

Name: AT FIRST
Description: When first seen or considered.

Name: INSTANTLY (IMMEDIATELY)
Description: Without delay.

Name: NEXT TO
Description: To be positioned adjacent to.

Name: BECAUSE OF
Description: Undergo decomposition.

Name: STILL (CONTINUING)
Description: Continuance of motion or state.

Name: SUDDENLY
Description: Happening unexpectedly.

Name: THEN
Description: Soon after that.

Name: AT THAT TIME
Description: At a certain time in the past.

Name: THITHER (THERE TO)
Description: Directed towards this place there.

Name: A LITTLE
Description: More than one, but not as much as usual or as expected. (for mass nouns)

Name: HITHER (HERE TO)
Description: Directed towards this place here.

Name: HARDLY
Description: Barely perceivable or noticeable.

Name: FROM HERE
Description: Directed from here towards another direction.

Name: WHITHER (WHERE TO)
Description: Directed to what location?

Name: BENEFIT
Description: The profit of some action.

Name: BOSS
Description: A boss is a person in charge, or a supervisor.

Name: BUSINESS
Description: A business is an organizational entity involved in the provision of goods and services to consumers.

Name: COLD (CHILL)
Description: Cold is the presence of low temperature, especially in the atmosphere.

Name: CONVERSATION
Description: Conversation is interactive, communication between two or more people.

Name: CUCKOO
Description: The cuckoos are a family of birds, Cuculidae, the sole taxon in the order Cuculiformes.

Name: CURRENT (STREAM)
Description: A current, in a river or stream, is the flow of water influenced by gravity as the water moves downhill to reduce its potential energy.

Name: ELEVATION
Description: The elevation of a geographic location is its height above or below a fixed reference point, most commonly a reference geoid, a mathematical model of the Earth's sea level as an equipotential gravitational surface (see Geodetic system, vertical datum).

Name: FAIRY TALE
Description: A fairy tale is a type of short story that typically features folkloric fantasy characters, such as dwarves, dragons, elves, fairies, giants, gnomes, goblins, griffins, mermaids, talking animals, trolls, unicorns, or witches, and usually magic or enchantments.

Name: FLAVOR
Description: Flavor is the sensory impression of food or other substance, and is determined primarily by the chemical senses of taste and smell.

Name: FLOCK (OF ANIMALS)
Description: A large number of animals, especially birds, sheep or goats.

Name: GATE
Description: A gate or gateway is a point of entry to a space which is enclosed by walls.

Name: HAPPINESS
Description: In philosophy, happiness translates the Greek concept of eudaimonia, and refers to the good life, or flourishing, rather than simply an emotion.

Name: HOARFROST
Description: Refers to white ice crystals, deposited on the ground or loosely attached to exposed objects such as wires or leaves.

Name: BUNDLE
Description: A group of things fastened together.

Name: CALL (APPEAL)
Description: An act of calling with the voice.

Name: COUNT (QUANTITY)
Description: The total number of individual things in a given unit or sample obtained by counting all or a subsample of them.

Name: CRADLE
Description: A bed for a baby.

Name: DAMAGE (INJURY)
Description: Loss or harm resulting from injury to person or objects.

Name: GAP (DISTANCE)
Description: A separation in space.

Name: LAIR
Description: The resting or living place of a wild animal.

Name: MEANING
Description: The thing one intends to convey especially by language.

Name: POUCH
Description: A small bag.

Name: SLAB
Description: Thick plate or slice.

Name: SLEEVE
Description: Part of a garment covering the arm.

Name: SLICE
Description: A thin flat piece cut from something.

Name: STATE (POLITICS)
Description: A politically organized body of people usually occupying a definite territory.

Name: TUBE
Description: Cylindrical structure or device.

Name: WARE
Description: Manufactured articles.

Name: LAUGHTER
Description: Laughter is a physical reaction in humans and some other species of primate, consisting typically of rhythmical, often audible contractions of the diaphragm and other parts of the respiratory system.

Name: LEASH
Description: A leash is a rope or similar material attached to the neck or head of an animal for restraint or control.

Name: LONGING (WISH)
Description: The strong desire for something.

Name: MESSAGE
Description: A message is a discrete unit of communication intended by the source for consumption by some recipient or group of recipients.

Name: MOORLAND
Description: Moorland or moor is a type of habitat found in upland areas in temperate grasslands, savannas, and shrublands and montane grasslands and shrublands biomes, characterised by low-growing vegetation on acidic soils.

Name: NET
Description: A grid-like device or object.

Name: NEWS
Description: News is information about current events.

Name: PAW
Description: A paw is the soft foot of a mammal, generally a quadruped, that has claws.

Name: PERCH (FISH)
Description: Perch is a common name for fish of the genus Perca, freshwater gamefish belonging to the family Percidae.

Name: PIKE (FISH)
Description: The northern pike is a species of carnivorous fish of the genus Esox (the pikes).

Name: REASON
Description: Reason is the capacity for consciously making sense of things, applying logic, establishing and verifying facts, and changing or justifying practices, institutions, and beliefs based on new or existing information.

Name: RIBBON
Description: A ribbon is a thin band of material, typically cloth but also plastic or sometimes metal, used primarily as decorative binding and tying.

Name: RIDDLE
Description: A riddle is a statement or question or phrase having a double or veiled meaning, put forth as a puzzle to be solved.

Name: SIN
Description: In a religious context, sin is the act of violating God's will by transgressing his commandments.

Name: SLEEP (STATE)
Description: Sleep is a naturally recurring state of mind and body characterized by altered consciousness, relatively inhibited sensory activity, inhibition of nearly all voluntary muscles, and reduced interactions with surroundings.

Name: STRAP
Description: A strap is an elongated flap or ribbon, usually of fabric or leather.

Name: SWARM (OF BIRDS)
Description: Swarm behaviour, or swarming, is a collective behaviour exhibited by entities, particularly animals, of similar size which aggregate together, perhaps milling about the same spot or perhaps moving en masse or migrating in some direction.

Name: THOUGHT
Description: Thought refers to ideas or arrangements of ideas that are the result of the process of thinking.

Name: VIOLENCE
Description: Violence is defined by the World Health Organization as *the intentional use of physical force or power, threatened or actual, against oneself, another person, or against a group or community, which either results in or has a high likelihood of resulting in injury, death, psychological harm, maldevelopment, or deprivation*, although the group acknowledges that the inclusion of *the use of power* in its definition expands on the conventional understanding of the word.

Name: WORKER
Description: Somebody who works.

Name: DISTANCE
Description: Distance is a numerical description of how far apart objects are.

Name: WALK (MANNER)
Description: The act of walking, the way one walks.

Name: AREA
Description: Area is the quantity that expresses the extent of a two-dimensional figure or shape, or planar lamina, in the plane.

Name: ITEM
Description: Any object that can be grasped.

Name: GIFT
Description: A gift or a present is an item given to someone without the expectation of payment or return.

Name: COMPANIONSHIP
Description: An interpersonal relationship is a strong, deep, or close association or acquaintance between two or more people that may range in duration from brief to enduring.

Name: HEAP
Description: A collection of things thrown one on another.

Name: HEIGHT
Description: Height is the measure of vertical distance, either how tall something is, or how high up it is.

Name: CAMPFIRE
