Name: STURGEON
Description: A common name denoting a fish of the Acipenseridae family.

Name: MOCCASIN
Description: A shoe with a soft sole made from animal skin or leather.

Name: WARRIOR
Description: A person trained in combat or warfare.

Name: TOWN OR VILLAGE
Description: Referring to either smaller (village) or larger (town) settlements.

Name: MALLARD
Description: A member of the Anatidae family, common in large parts of the world and native to the northern hemisphere.

Name: AMERICAN BLACK BEAR
Description: A member of the Urisdae family (Ursus americanus) native to North America.

Name: INDIGENOUS PEOPLES OF THE AMERICAS
Description: Referring to the native inhabitants of North and South America.

Name: LOWER BACK
Description: The lower part of the spine, also known as the lumbar region, which is situated between the rib cage and the pelvis.

Name: PANT
Description: To breathe quickly and loudly as a result of running or exercising.

Name: BLEED
Description: To lose blood because of a disease or an injury.

Name: FAINT (PASS OUT)
Description: To become unconscious as a result of a temporary decrease in the blood supply to the brain.

Name: STUMBLE
Description: To step awkwardly or to catch your foot on something and almost fall.

Name: STAMP
Description: To put your foot down on the ground heavily and noisily; to walk in this way.

Name: LEAN
Description: To bend or move from a vertical position or to make something do that.

Name: SLEEPY
Description: Feeling tired and willing to go to sleep.

Name: DISABLED PERSON
Description: A person with a physical condition or mental disorder that is characterized by physical, sensory, cognitive or intellectual impairment.

Name: BURN (INJURY)
Description: An injury caused by exposure to heat, fire or chemical agents.

Name: INTESTINAL WORM
Description: An organism, also known as the parasitic worm, that infects and breeds in the gastrointestinal tract of humans and animals.

Name: LEPROSY
Description: An infectious disease caused by the bacteria Mycobacterium leprae that affects the skin as well as the peripheral nerves.

Name: HEADACHE
Description: A pain in the head.

Name: KNOW
Description: To have met and recognize somebody or to be certain or sure about something.

Name: SURPRISE (SOMEBODY)
Description: To make someone feel surprised by giving, telling or doing something unexpected.

Name: HONOR (SOMEBODY)
Description: To treat someone with the utmost respect and admiration.

Name: HESITATE
Description: To hold back from saying or doing something because of doubt or uncertainty.

Name: PLAN
Description: A method or a set of arrangements, needed to achieve a specific goal.

Name: PRETEND
Description: To behave in such a way that makes someone believe something that is not true.

Name: GENEROUS
Description: Willing to give more than expected, especially money.

Name: CURIOUS
Description: Having a strong desire to learn about things and people around.

Name: STUBBORN
Description: Unyielding; unlikely to change one's mind and determined not to be influenced by someone else's opinion.

Name: ADULT
Description: A fully grown and mature person.

Name: CO-WIFE
Description: Another female partner in a polygamous marriage.

Name: WEAVER
Description: A person whose occupation is weaving cloth, carpets, or baskets.

Name: ASSEMBLE (GET TOGETHER)
Description: To come together in a group.

Name: AVOID
Description: To keep away from somebody or something.

Name: GOSSIP
Description: To talk about other people's private lives.

Name: SLANDER
Description: To make a false statement about someone with the intention to defame them or damage their reputation.

Name: COMPLAIN
Description: To express one's dissatisfaction or unhappiness.

Name: AGREE
Description: To have the same opinion as someone else.

Name: AGREEMENT
Description: The state of sharing the same feeling or opinion.

Name: PERSUADE
Description: To convince someone to do something by giving them good reasons to do so.

Name: PROVERB
Description: A widely known and used phrase or sentence, giving advice or reflecting something commonly experienced.

Name: TICKLE (SOMEBODY)
Description: To move your fingers lightly on a sensitive part of somebody's body to make them feel uncomfortable and cause them to laugh.

Name: SERVE (SOMEONE)
Description: To perform the duties of a servant.

Name: PUNISH
Description: To inflict pain, suffering or loss on somebody who has broken a law or done something wrong.

Name: APPLY (OINTMENT)
Description: To put and spread some substance on the skin.

Name: MUSH (FOOD)
Description: A kind of porridge that is prepared by boiling it with water or milk until thick.

Name: FERMENT
Description: To undergo the chemical change characterized by the conversion of sugars into alcohol under the influence of enzymes.

Name: COOKING POT
Description: A vessel, usually with a rounded body, used to cook food.

Name: TAKE OUT
Description: To remove or pull something out of an enclosed space.

Name: STORE UP
Description: To put something somewhere and keep it there for future use.

Name: PACK
Description: To put something in a container so that it could be carried or transported.

Name: GRANARY
Description: A building for storing threshed grain.

Name: BELLOWS
Description: A device that consists of a flexible leather air valve which can be expanded or contracted by operating the two handles, located on the opposite sides. It has many applications, especially blowing on a fire to supply it with air.

Name: POLISH (SOMETHING)
Description: To make something smooth and shiny by rubbing it with a cloth.

Name: SHELL (SOMETHING)
Description: To remove the hard outer covering from nuts, peas, eggs, etc.

Name: RICH PERSON
Description: A wealthy person; a person with abundant possessions.

Name: POOR PERSON
Description: A person with little or no possessions or money.

Name: COWRIE SHELL
Description: The shiny shell of marine gastropod mollusks from the family Cypraeidae, which have been used as currency or jewelry in some parts of the world.

Name: INHERIT
Description: To receive money, property or other possessions from somebody when they die.

Name: TRAVEL
Description: To make a journey, especially over a long distance.

Name: WANDER
Description: To walk around idly without a specific purpose and direction.

Name: LOST
Description: Not knowing where you are and unable to find the way.

Name: PADDLE (MOVEMENT)
Description: To make a boat move by pushing a pole with a wide end through the water.

Name: LOAD (SOMETHING)
Description: To put a large quantity of things onto something.

Name: PLUNDER
Description: To steal goods or valuables with force, especially during a war or civil disorder.

Name: HUM
Description: To sing a tune with the mouth closed.

Name: DIVORCE (SEPARATE)
Description: To end one's marriage by a legal process.

Name: MOURNING
Description: The feeling of great sadness because someone has died.

Name: ANTELOPE
Description: Any of even-toed deer-like mammals of the family Bovidae, indigenous to various parts of Africa and Eurasia.

Name: ZEBRA
Description: Any of several species of genus Equus with distinctive black-and-white striped coats, native to Africa.

Name: SHREW
Description: Any of small, mole-like mammals with a long pointed snout from the family Soricidae of the order Eulipotyphla.

Name: MONGOOSE
Description: A common name for several species of tropical ferret-like carnivorous mammals, distinguished by a long body and tail.

Name: ELEPHANT TRUNK
Description: A long, tube-shaped nose of an elephant.

Name: GROWL
Description: To make a low sound in the throat, usually as a sign of anger.

Name: RUMINATE
Description: (Of an animal) to chew the food brought back from the stomach and partially digested.

Name: PARTRIDGE
Description: Any of medium-sized non-migratory birds of the Phasianidae family, smaller than the pheasant but bigger than the quail.

Name: PERCH (OF BIRD)
Description: To land and rest on a perch, branch, fence, etc.

Name: CACKLE
Description: To produce an unpleasant, sharp sound, characteristic of a hen, especially after laying an egg.

Name: PECK
Description: (Of a bird) to move the beak forward quickly to strike, bite, or pick up something.

Name: HISS
Description: To produce a continuous voiceless sibilant sound like a long /s/.

Name: CORN HUSK
Description: The outer covering of a corncob.

Name: DESERT
Description: A barren area of landscape, typically covered with sand, characterized by little precipitation and hostile living conditions for plant and animal life.

Name: MARSH
Description: A muddy and poorly drained area of land, usually near a lake or a river.

Name: BUBBLE
Description: A small ball of air or gas in a liquid.

Name: FULL MOON
Description: The lunar phase when the moon is fully illuminated by the sun and appears in the sky as a full circle.

Name: NEW MOON
Description: The lunar phase when the moon appears in the sky as a slender crescent shortly after its conjunction with the sun.

Name: SQUEAK
Description: To make a short, high-pitched sound.

Name: HOT WEATHER
Description: A period of unusually high temperatures.

Name: COLD WEATHER
Description: A period of time, characterized by low temperatures.

Name: MOVEMENT
Description: A change of position or place.

Name: THROW AWAY
Description: To get rid of something one no longer needs.

Name: DIP
Description: To put something partially in a liquid for a short time and take it out again.

Name: SINGE
Description: To burn the surface of something slightly, usually by mistake, in a way that it does not catch fire; to be burnt this way.

Name: CONTINUE
Description: To carry on with something or to keep existing or happening.

Name: LENGTHEN
Description: To become longer or to make something longer.

Name: HOLLOW
Description: Having an empty space inside.

Name: SLIPPERY
Description: Smooth or wet so that it is difficult to hold or stand on it.

Name: STICKY
Description: Covered with some substance so that it sticks to anything that touches it.

Name: ODOR (SMELL)
Description: The property of something that can be perceived and recognized through the nose.

Name: SCATTER
Description: To throw or drop things in different directions so that they cover a large area.

Name: DARK YELLOW
Description: A darker variant of the primary color yellow, mixed with black, orange or red.

Name: BEIGE
Description: A kind of yellowish color, mixed with gray.

Name: FEELING SORE
Description: A part of the body causes pain and discomfort.

Name: BRILLIANT
Description: (Of a color) having a high saturation and reflecting a considerable amount of light.

Name: CLEAR (TO SEE)
Description: If something is visible without obstacles (e.g., clouds, spots).

Name: TIE (NOUN)
Description: A small band of fabric which is tied around the collar of a shirt.

Name: RAINCOAT
Description: A long jacket which is waterproof.

Name: PHARYNX
Description: The inner part of the neck which starts after the oral and nasal cavity.

Name: LARYNX
Description: Organ on the upper end of the trachea.

Name: BELLYBUTTON
Description: The middle of the belly where the umbilical cord has grown in the womb during pregnancy.

Name: OVARY
Description: The female sex organ which is often paired and produces eggs for procreation.

Name: BADGER
Description: A mammal which belong to the family Mustelidae.

Name: GUINEA PIG
Description: A tailless rodent which is larger than a hamster and often kept as a pet. It belongs to the family Caviidae.

Name: MARMOT
Description: A rodent of the genera Marmota.

Name: BUDGERIGAR
Description: A bird which is often kept as a pet and belongs to the species of Melopsittacus undulatus.

Name: FINCH
Description: A bird with a conical beak of the family Fringillidae.

Name: FLAMINGO
Description: A bird with deep pink colored feathers of the family Phoenicopteridae.

Name: NIGHTINGALE
Description: A bird which is famous for its singing of the family Muscicapidae.

Name: STORK
Description: A bird with long legs, a long beak and often black and with feathers of the family Ciconiidae.

Name: AVOCADO
Description: A fruit with a soft, greenish peel and a brown round seed in the middle of a tree from the family Persea americana.

Name: BROCCOLI
Description: A plant of the cabbage family, Brassicaceae, which is shaped like a tree.

Name: CELERY
Description: A vegetable with a long greenish stalk of the carrot family.

Name: COURGETTE
Description: A long green marrow of Cucurbita pepo.

Name: LETTUCE
Description: A often green plant, Lactuca sativa, which is mainly used in salads.

Name: APRICOT
Description: A fruit of orange color with a fuzzy peel and a black seed inside, similar to a peach or plum of a tree from the family Prunus armeniaca.

Name: LYCHEE
Description: A tropical fruit with a hard brownish peel with a black seed in the inside and with flesh of a tree from the soapberry family.

Name: POMEGRANATE
Description: A fruit with a thick reddish peel and many small red little seeds of a tree from the family Punica granatum.

Name: FERRY
Description: A transport ship used for small distances from one port to another which often runs on a regular schedule.

Name: CHIMPANZEE
Description: A great ape which is native to Africa and is suggested to be the closest extant relative to humans.

Name: NEAR (IN SPACE)
Description: Not far distant in space.

Name: INSTEP
Description: The arched part of the human foot between the ankle and the toes.

Name: BAREFOOT
Description: Not wearing anything on the feet.

Name: GRIZZLY BEAR
Description: A large and ferocious subspecies of the brown bear, inhabiting North America.

Name: MARTEN
Description: A mammal of the family Mustelidae in the genus Martes, inhabiting the forests of the Northern Hemisphere, having a long, slender body, a bushy tail and short legs and also known for its thick, valuable fur.

Name: WHIRLWIND
Description: A rapidly rotating, tall column of air, moving over land or sea and causing damage.

Name: BATTLE CRY (WAR WHOOP)
Description: A shout, used by warriors in battle with the purpose of arousing aggression on their own side or intimidating the enemy.

Name: POCKETKNIFE
Description: A small knife with one or more blades that fold back into the handle.

Name: BRASS
Description: A yellow-colored metal made of the mixture of copper and zinc and used in the making of decorations and musical instruments.

Name: INTERPRETER
Description: A person who translates someone's speech orally from one language into another.

Name: CRANE (DEVICE)
Description: A device for lifting and moving heavy objects, typically consisting of a moving boom, beam, or gantry from which lifting gear is suspended.

Name: VASE
Description: An often round vessel which is used for decoration or for holding cut flowers.

Name: SHAPE
Description: The form of an object or person which refers to its outline.

Name: DROP (OF A LIQUID)
Description: A small amount of a liquid that falls in a round shape.

Name: HATE (LOATHING)
Description: A strong feeling of dislike for something or somebody.

Name: KHAKI
Description: A yellowish-brown color which is often associated with military uniforms.

Name: BRIGHT YELLOW
Description: A very intense variant of the color yellow.

Name: LILAC
Description: A light variant of the color purple which resembles the color of the flowers of a Syringa tree.

Name: MAGENTA
Description: A variant of the color red but deeper and mixed with purple.

Name: TRANSPARENT
Description: If a substance or object permits the uninterrupted passage of light and one can see through it.

Name: MOUNTAINOUS
Description: A landscape with lots of mountains.

Name: FLORAL
Description: A design or landscape which incorporates representations of flowers.

Name: MUGGY
Description: A type of weather when it is hot and the air is damp.

Name: WINDY
Description: When there is a lot of wind.

Name: FOGGY
Description: A thick layer of fog.

Name: THUNDERY
Description: Sounds that resemble thunder.

Name: EMOTIONAL
Description: Having any strong feeling, as of joy, sorrow, or fear.

Name: SAFE
Description: Having a feeling of security or protection from harm.

Name: PATERNAL UNCLE
Description: Father's brother or father's sibling's husband.

Name: BAD OR EVIL
Description: Not good; unfavorable; negative, or intending to harm or being/acting ethically wrong.

Name: STORING POT
Description: A vessel used for storing food or liquids.

Name: WATER POT
Description: A vessel used for storing water.

Name: RICE SEEDLING
Description: The seedling of a rice plant.

Name: POUND (FOOD)
Description: To prepare food with a pounding or beating movement, for example, pre-processing of grain or of sago.

Name: GRAPEVINE
Description: A climbing plant that produces grapes and belongs to the family Vitaceae.

Name: ONE HUNDRED AND TWO
Description: The natural number one hundred and two (102).

Name: ONE HUNDRED AND ELEVEN
Description: The natural number one hundred and eleven (111).

Name: TWO HUNDRED AND TEN
Description: The natural number two hundred and ten (210).

Name: ONE THOUSAND AND ONE
Description: The natural number one thousand and one (1001).

Name: ONE THOUSAND AND TWO
Description: The natural number one thousand and two (1002).

Name: ONE THOUSAND AND SIXTY
Description: The natural number one thousand and sixty (1060).

Name: TWO THOUSAND AND TWO
Description: The natural number two thousand and two (2002).

Name: CATFISH
Description: Any of ray-finned fish with long stiff barbels, resembling a cat's whiskers. There are diverse types of catfish, ranging in size and appearance and inhabiting mostly freshwater environments.

Name: DAUGHTER (OF MALE EGO)
Description: A daughter, as referred to by her father.

Name: SON (OF MALE EGO)
Description: A son, as referred to by his father.

Name: PET
Description: An animal or a bird that is kept at home for companionship rather than for practical use.

Name: SISTER-IN-LAW (OF FEMALE EGO)
Description: The sister of a woman's husband or the wife of a woman's brother.

Name: GRANDCHILD (OF FEMALE EGO)
Description: The child in the second generation in relation to a female individual.

Name: ONE HUNDRED AND THREE
Description: The natural number one hundred and three (103).

Name: ONE HUNDRED AND EIGHT
Description: The natural number one hundred and eight (108).

Name: TWO HUNDRED AND TWO
Description: The natural number two hundred and two (202).

Name: TWO HUNDRED AND THIRTY ONE
Description: The natural number two hundred and thirty-one (231).

Name: TWO HUNDRED AND FORTY
Description: The natural number two hundred and forty (240).

Name: TWO HUNDRED AND FIFTY
Description: The natural number two hundred and fifty (250).

Name: THREE HUNDRED AND FOUR
Description: The natural number three hundred and four (304).

Name: ONE THOUSAND AND TWENTY SEVEN
Description: The natural number one thousand and twenty-seven (1027).

Name: ONE THOUSAND TWO HUNDRED
Description: The natural number one thousand two hundred (1200).

Name: SIX THOUSAND
Description: The natural number six thousand (6000).

Name: EIGHT THOUSAND
Description: The natural number eight thousand (8000).

Name: TWO MILLION
Description: The natural number two million (2000000).

Name: DARK GREEN
Description: A darker variant of the color green, mixed with black, with an approximate wavelength between 543 and 549 nm.

Name: ALBATROSS
Description: Any seabird of the family Diomedeidae. Some species are among the largest flying birds in the world.

Name: OSTRICH
Description: Any of two species of large, flightless birds in the family Struthionidae, native to Africa.

Name: STINGER
Description: The pointed stinging organ of an animal, usually an insect, which is able to penetrate skin. Sometimes used to inject poison.

Name: FISHBONE
Description: Any of the bones forming the skeleton of a fish, especially one of the sharp slender bones attached to the backbone.

Name: IVORY
Description: The hard, white substance which forms the tusks of animals like elephants, narwhals, or walruses and is often considered a valuable material.

Name: DATE (FRUIT)
Description: The sweet, edible fruit of the date palm Phoenix dactylifera of the family Arecaceae.

Name: FERN
Description: Any member of a large group of vascular plants in the family Filices who have neither flowers nor seeds.

Name: RASPBERRY
Description: The edible, berry-like fruit of a multitude of plant species in the genus Rubus of the family Rosaceae, most typically red, small and sweet.

Name: GRAPEFRUIT OR POMELO
Description: The fruit of the pomelo tree, Citrus maxima, of the family Rutaceae, or the fruit of the grapefruit tree, Citrus x paradisi, a citrus hybrid which originated from crossing pomelos and oranges. Due to the recent origin of the grapefruit and the close genetic relatedness between both fruits, they are often not differentiated lexically.

Name: SHY OR ASHAMED
Description: The feeling of being uncomfortable with attracting attention or feeling shame or guilt.

Name: RIPE OR COOKED
Description: Suitable for eating because it is fully grown (of fruit and crops) or because it has been boiled, fried, grilled, etc.

Name: EYEBALL
Description: The partly visible orb nesting in the eye socket which contains for example pupil, retina and iris and is connected to the brain via the optic nerve.

Name: JUNGLE
Description: A type of forest with thick and overgrown ground vegetation, typically associated with tropical or humid climate zones.

Name: SCREAM (PRODUCE A CRY)
Description: To give a loud cry out of pain, fear or excitement. The vocalisation resulted from screaming is distinct from that produced by shrieking in that it is typically characterized by a longer duration and lower pitch.

Name: BOULDER
Description: A large rock fragment of natural origin, usually too heavy to be moved by a single person.

Name: MIRITI PALM
Description: Mauritia flexuosa, a palm tree of the family Arecaceae, common to tropical regions of South America.

Name: COWARDLY
Description: Not being brave or courageous; an attribute describing someone who is easily frightened or disheartened in the face of difficulty or danger.

Name: DISOBEDIENT
Description: Refusing to obey what someone in authority is requesting.

Name: HANDSOME
Description: Used to describe a person that is attractive and pleasing in appearance.

Name: ALMOND
Description: The edible and cultivated fruit of the tree Prunus dulcis in the family Rosaceae. It resembles a nut and can be sold shelled or unshelled.

Name: WAXING MOON
Description: The phase in the lunar cycle between new moon and full moon when the illuminated area increases.

Name: WANING MOON
Description: The phase in the lunar cycle between full moon and new moon when the illuminated area decreases.

Name: HOT (FEELING HOT)
Description: The subjective feeling of an increased body temperature.

Name: COLD (FEELING COLD)
Description: The subjective feeling of a decreased body temperature.

Name: CALM (OF SEA)
Description: A situation in which a body of water is free from disturbance and without wind or waves.

Name: BROOK
Description: A very shallow flowing body of water smaller than a creek that can easily be crossed.

Name: MALE COUSIN
Description: The male child of the sibling of a parent of a person.

Name: FEMALE COUSIN
Description: The female child of the sibling of a parent of a person.

Name: HINNY
Description: The offspring of a stallion (male horse) and a female donkey (jenny).

Name: MALE CAT
Description: A male of the Felis catus species.

Name: ROE DEER
Description: Member of the species Capreolus capreolus widespread in Europe. Smaller than other deer and characterised by its red and grey-brown colour.

Name: PREGNANT (OF ANIMALS)
Description: Describing an animal that is pregnant.

Name: HEALTHINESS
Description: Relating to the general state of health and well-being.

Name: DINNER (MAIN MEAL)
Description: Describing the main meal of the day.

Name: WALL
Description: A supporting structure for different types of constructions, e.g. houses and huts, or a construction to enclose and separate areas.

Name: RENT (SOMETHING)
Description: To have temporary possession of premises (apartments) or objects.

Name: PUT (IN A SITTING POSITION)
Description: To put someone or oneself in a sitting position.

Name: PUT (IN A STANDING POSITION)
Description: To put someone or oneself in a standing position.

Name: LOVE (AFFECTION)
Description: A feeling of affection and fondness for someone.

Name: BE CALLED BY NAME
Description: To have a specific name or be named something or be called something.

Name: HALF (HALF OF)
Description: Describing one of the two equal parts into which something may be divided.

Name: ASTRINGENT
Description: A property describing a substance which causes the skin, membranes, or other tissue to contract. Tannins in unripe fruit are known to function as astringents.

Name: HANDSPAN
Description: The distance between splayed out thumb and little finger or index finger of a human hand. Formerly used as a unit of measurement or for roughly gauging small lengths around 20 centimeters.

Name: BROAD BEAN
Description: Bean of the plant Vicia faba, also known as fava bean. It is typically large, of a pale green colour, and edible.

Name: CRANBERRY
Description: The red and typically sour berry of several evergreen shrubs in the family Ericaceae.

Name: WINDMILL
Description: A large structure or building with long revolving blades or sails that is used for converting wind energy in order to produce electricity or to directly power an attached mechanical construction for grinding.

Name: ONE THIRD
Description: One of three equal parts of a whole.

Name: BUT
Description: A coordinating expression that signals a contrast to what was previously said, e.g. disagreement or a further point to consider.

Name: CONTEMPT
Description: A feeling of ultimate disgust and a complete lack of respect towards somebody.

Name: DISAPPOINTMENT
Description: A feeling of sadness because something did not happen the way it was expected or did not happen at all.

Name: EXCITEMENT
Description: A feeling of extreme but short-term happiness.

Name: INTEREST (FEELING)
Description: A desire to learn about something or somebody.

Name: SURPRISE (FEELING)
Description: A feeling caused by something unexpected.

Name: TRIUMPH
Description: A feeling of extreme pleasure and excitement as a result of success or a victory.

Name: AMUSEMENT
Description: A feeling caused by doing or watching something entertaining or funny.

Name: AWE
Description: A feeling of deep respect mixed with slight fear or wonder.

Name: CONCENTRATION
Description: The ability to direct all the attention to one thing or activity.

Name: CONFUSION
Description: A feeling of uncertainty about what to do or what is happening.

Name: SADNESS
Description: A feeling of being unhappy because something is missing or wrong.

Name: ITCH (CAUSE ITCHING OR FEEL ITCHY)
Description: To have an unpleasant sensation on the skin that provokes the need to scratch; to be the cause of this sensation.

Name: ITCH OR ITCHY OR ITCHING
Description: To have an unpleasant sensation on the skin that provokes the need to scratch or to be the cause of this sensation; the result of itching, i.e. an unpleasant sensation on the skin, or the property of having or producing such a sensation.

Name: EGGSHELL
Description: The calcareous covering protecting the inside of an egg.

Name: CONFUSED
Description: Being in a state of not exactly knowing or understanding what is happening; bewildered; perplexed.

Name: MIDWIFE
Description: A person, usually a woman, who helps women in childbirth and provides ante- and postnatal care.

Name: POSSESSIONS
Description: The totality of things that someone owns; their property or belongings.

Name: FAIL
Description: Not succeeding in an endeavour (of persons) or to stop working as intended (of objects).

Name: HEAR OR LISTEN
Description: To perceive sound with the ear, with or without paying attention to it.

Name: OTHER OR SOME
Description: The rest of a group or an unspecified quantity or number.

Name: HURT OR PAIN
Description: To experience an unpleasant physical sensation that is often the result of an injury, disease or other ailment; an unpleasant physical sensation itself.

Name: BARK OR SHELL
Description: Cover of the bodies of animals and plants, including the hard exterior part of mollusks, oysters, etc.

Name: ABORTION
Description: An intervention in a pregnancy by removal or expulsion of an embryo or fetus resulting in termination of the pregnancy.

Name: ALCOHOLIC (PERSON)
Description: A person who is affected by alcoholism in that they frequently drink alcohol which leads to addiction.

Name: ALLERGY
Description: A bodily reaction due to a hypersensitivity to an antigen or a pathological immunological reaction to substances, situations, or physical states.

Name: ANXIOUS
Description: To feel uneasiness of mind caused by anxiety.

Name: RUSTY
Description: Having been affected by rust.

Name: MURDERER
Description: A person who commits murder.

Name: BLOND
Description: A pale yellowish-brown color usually of hair.

Name: CHOCOLATE
Description: A food prepared from ground, roasted cocoa beans and often used to make candy.

Name: KNOWLEDGE
Description: The fact or state of knowing something or being familiar with a certain type of technique.

Name: CRIMINAL
Description: A person who committed a crime.

Name: DENTIST
Description: A person who is medically trained and licensed to practice the prevention, diagnosis, and treatment of diseases, injuries, and malformations of the teeth, jaws, and mouth.

Name: DEPRESSION
Description: A state of feeling sad that can become a chronic illness.

Name: DIAMOND
Description: The hardest known mineral on earth, consisting of crystalline carbon.

Name: IMAGINE
Description: To form a mental image of (something not present).

Name: FIGHT (COMBAT)
Description: A hostile encounter, such as a battle or combat.

Name: PISTOL
Description: A handgun with the chamber integral to its gun barrel.

Name: ROSE
Description: A showy flower of any of a genus (Rosa of the family Rosaceae, the rose family).

Name: NOISY
Description: To make a lot of noise.

Name: PATIENT
Description: Enduring difficult situations or a long waiting time with an even temper.

Name: IMPATIENT
Description: Becoming irritable in difficult situations or during long waiting times.

Name: TARANTULA
Description: Any large and hairy spider, typically of the Theraphosidae family, although some other spider species are subsumed under this name as well.

Name: NOBODY
Description: No person; not one member out of a group of people.

Name: SKUNK
Description: Mammals of the family Mephitidae, typically found in North and South America. These animals are known for their ability to spray attackers with a strong-smelling liquid.

Name: CUT OR HACK
Description: To perform an incision or chop something.

Name: NEPHEW OR NIECE
Description: A child of someone's brother or sister.

Name: EARHOLE
Description: The outer opening of the ear.

Name: ACQUIRE (SOMETHING)
Description: To come into possession of something, usually with an effort.

Name: AFFORD
Description: To have enough money to get something.

Name: ATTACH
Description: To fasten one thing to another.

Name: DETECT
Description: To notice or recognize something that is not particularly obvious.

Name: ROAR
Description: To make a deep loud cry (of lions and comparable wild animals); to make a deep loud cry, usually out of anger (of humans).

Name: NATURE
Description: The physical world including all living things as well as the land and the seas.

Name: ACCEPT
Description: To take or get something that was offered by someone.

Name: ATTACKING
Description: To use violence with the intention to harm.

Name: CLUMSY
Description: Moving carelessly or gracelessly, causing things to break or get knocked over.

Name: TAMING
Description: To domesticate an animal, bird, etc.; to make them used to living with and/or working for humans.

Name: TRUST (SOMEBODY)
Description: To have great confidence in someone that he or she is sincere, honest, and will not deliberately inflict any harm.

Name: SYMPATHIZE
Description: To show understanding for somebody's problems or hurt feelings.

Name: ENCOUNTER (MEET)
Description: To meet someone or discover something, usually unexpectedly.

Name: FATHER (OF A WOMAN)
Description: A male parent of a woman.

Name: FATHER (OF A MAN)
Description: A male parent of a man.

Name: MOTHER (OF A WOMAN)
Description: A female parent of a woman.

Name: MOTHER (OF A MAN)
Description: A female parent of a man.

Name: GRANDCHILD (SON'S OFFSPRING)
Description: Offspring of one's son.

Name: STEPCHILD
Description: The child of one's spouse and his or her previous partner.

Name: COW MILK
Description: The milk of cows.

Name: BREAST MILK
Description: The milk of humans.

Name: COUGH (ACT OF COUGHING)
Description: The act of coughing or the sound of coughing.

Name: TURQUOISE
Description: Having a light greenish blue as its color.

Name: PRIDE
Description: An emotional state of being proud.

Name: PLEASURE
Description: An emotional state of sensual gratification or frivolous amusement.

Name: DEVIL
Description: The personal supreme spirit of evil often represented in Christian belief as the tempter of humankind, the leader of all apostate angels, and the ruler of hell.

Name: CALABASH
Description: (Not to confuse with gourd) a plant from the family Bignoniaceae, native to tropical America. It has a form of a small tree, producing fruit of the globular shape. It is also known under the name of Crescentia cujete and its fruits are mostly used to make utensils, containers, and musical instruments.

Name: PEACH PALM
Description: A species of palm, also know as Bactris gasipaes, native to the tropical forests of Central and South America.

Name: GENIPA
Description: Either a species of trees in the family Rubiaceae native to the tropical forests of Americas or its fruit (also referred to as “genipap”). A Genipa tree typically has large smooth or hairy leaves and ovoid-shaped fruit with large and flat seeds.

Name: TINAMOU
Description: Any of the 47 sedentary, ground-dwelling bird species of the order Tinamiformes found in Central and South America. It bears a strong resemblance to patridges but has limited flight capability.

Name: PACU
Description: A freshwater species of fish belonging to the family Serrasalmidae and related to piranha.

Name: FEMALE ANIMAL
Description: A female animal (Noun)

Name: MALE ANIMAL
Description: A male animal (Noun)

Name: BABASSU PALM
Description: Type of palm (Attalea speciosa) widely spread in Brazil; its fruit is edible and used to produce oil and medicine

Name: BABY CARRIER
Description: A piece of cloth used around the body to carry a child

Name: BLUE-AND-YELLOW MACAW
Description: Type of bird commonly found in South America with blue and yellow feathers

Name: BRAZIL NUT
Description: Edible seed of a tree (bertholletia excelsa); used to produce medicine

Name: BRAZILIAN CEDAR
Description: Native Brazilian tree  (Cedrela odorata). Its wood is often used for canoes

Name: DAUGHTER (OF WOMAN)
Description: Daughter of a mother

Name: CECROPIA
Description: Common designation of several species of the Cecropia genus (genus Cecropia)

Name: GRIDIRON
Description: Wooden grill used to dry or smoke meat or fish

Name: HOPLIAS (GENUS)
Description: Genus of fish commonly found in South America

Name: INGA (GENUS)
Description: Genus of plants commonly found in Brazil

Name: LARGE-BULLET-ANT (subfamily Paraponerinae)
Description: Common designation for carnivorous ants of the Paraponerinae subfamily

Name: MOUNTAIN SOURSOP (Annona montana)
Description: Type of tree found in the Amazon

Name: PIUM (SIMULIIDAE)
Description: Hematophagous black fly found in tropical countries

Name: RED-AND-GREEN MACAW
Description: Type of bird commonly found in South America with predominantly red plumage

Name: SON OF WOMAN
Description: Son of a mother

Name: TAPIOCA
Description: Starch extracted from the root of manioc

Name: TAYRA (EIRA BARBARA)
Description: Omnivorous animal from South and Central America

Name: WAX
Description: Organic solid compounds of animals or vegetal origin

Name: WRISTBAND
Description: An article used as an adornment around the wrist

Name: LOWER LIP
Description: The lower fleshy protrusion around the opening of the mouth.

Name: ORION'S CONSTELLATION
Description: A constellation of stars visible from around the world.

Name: BABY SLING
Description: A piece of cloth used for carrying an infant or small child around a carer's body.

Name: HONEYCOMB
Description: A wax structure consisting of multiple small holes made by bees to store their honey.

Name: SHOTGUN
Description: A long gun (used mainly for hunting) that shoots multiple small bullets at a time.

Name: RED-FOOTED TORTOISE
Description: A medium-sized species of tortoise (Chelonoidis Carbonarius), found in northern parts of South America.

Name: LIBER (INNER BARK)
Description: The inner most layer of bark (particularly from a tree).

Name: PANDA
Description: Also *giant panda*, a white-and-black mammal of the *Ailuropoda* family, native to eastern Asia, commonly referred to as a type of bear.

Name: REFRIGERATOR
Description: A storage box, compartment or room to stock goods by means of mechanical refrigeration.

Name: CHARITY
Description: A benevolent action in favor of the needy, or an activity or gift for the benefit of the public.

Name: FRIENDSHIP
Description: A feeling of affection, good disposition, and sympathy experienced towards someone.

Name: HOSTILITY
Description: An aversion, feeling of rivalry, or aggressiveness experienced by an individual or group towards another.

Name: DISPUTE
Description: A disagreement or contentious argument between parties, typically in a political or ideological sense.

Name: SYSTEM
Description: A set of connected elements that form a whole by virtue of their interrelatedness and function.

Name: SOCIETY
Description: A large social body brought together and organized under a common set of rules or principles.

Name: RELATIONSHIP
Description: The way in which two elements or individuals are connected, usually in a social or affective sense.

Name: IDENTITY
Description: A persisting state of being the same for an entity or someone, from an objective or a subjective standpoint. Commonly referring to an individual's self-sense of being as a distinct person.

Name: TEAM
Description: A cooperative group of individuals working together for a common purpose.

Name: DISCIPLINE
Description: The ability and training of self-control and diligence, usually in abiding by a set of rules.

Name: SCENERY
Description: The appearance of a landscape, in particular natural and aesthetically pleasing.

Name: SPLENDOR
Description: The aesthetic and moral quality of being splendid, magnificent, or grand.

Name: TRAUMA
Description: A physical wound and, in particular, a psychological state of pain, ensued from a harmful experience of set of events.

Name: CONCEPT
Description: A particular object of thought formulated as an abstract or general idea.

Name: CONTENT
Description: In its physical sense, substance held by a recipient. In its cognitive sense, information or substance matter of a given subject.

Name: EFFECT
Description: The manifestation of the particular influence of a given action on something.

Name: RESULT
Description: The final outcome or consequence of a causal chain, operation or set of circumstances.

Name: PROCESS
Description: A systematic and continuous course of actions and changes, which can be goal-directed or spontaneous.

Name: METHOD
Description: A specific technique or way of performing an action to achieve a particular goal.

Name: EXCITED
Description: Arousal or a feeling of enthusiasm about something.

Name: DEPRESSED
Description: A mental state of despondency, unhappinness, or hopelessness.

Name: UNHAPPY
Description: Feeling not cheerful or glad, sometimes due to a misfortune.

Name: NERVOUS
Description: A mental state of nervousness or agitation. Also, being easily excited or irritated.

Name: EXPLODE
Description: To burst violently as a result of internal pressure.

Name: SHINY
Description: Property of a surface that is bright from reflected light.

Name: COMPANION
Description: One who accompanies or associates with another, either habitually or casually.

Name: TADPOLE
Description: Larval stage of amphibians.

Name: GET DRUNK
Description: Activity of drinking alcoholic beverages that leads to having an altered conciousness.

Name: GUAVA
Description: Fruit from the myrtle family, native to Latin America.

Name: BREEZE
Description: A gentle to moderate wind.

Name: RED DEER
Description: The red deer (Cervus elaphus) is one of the largest deer species. A male red deer is called a stag or hart, and a female is called a hind. Red deer are ruminants, characterized by a four-chambered stomach. Genetic evidence indicates that the red deer, as traditionally defined, is a species group, rather than a single species, though exactly how many species the group includes remains disputed.

Name: THESE (PLURAL OF THIS)
Description: The indicated objects, items, etc. close to the speaker.

Name: THOSE (PLURAL OF THAT)
Description: The indicated objects, items, etc. distant from the speaker.

Name: COLLAPSE
Description: To fall down suddenly because of pressure or having no strength or support.

Name: HOARSE
Description: (Of a voice or a person) Having a rough voice, often because of a sore throat or a cold.

Name: PLATEAU
Description: A large flat area of land that is high above sea level.

Name: AGAVE
Description: A plant that grows in the hot, dry parts of the southern US and South America. There are many different types of agave and the plants have thick long or rounded leaves with sharp points on them, and tall flowers.

Name: LAWN
Description: An area of grass, especially near to a house or in a park, that is cut regularly to keep it short.

Name: TORTILLA
Description: A thin, flat bread made from maize flour, eaten hot or cold, typically with a savoury filling.

Name: SARDINE
Description: A pilchard or other fish in the herring family.

Name: JINGLE (INSTRUMENT)
Description: One of a cluster of small bells, shaken or tapped on the palm of the player's hand. The small metal discs arranged around the frame of a tambourine are also called "jingles".

Name: PIANO (INSTRUMENT)
Description: A large musical instrument with a row of black and white keys that are pressed to play notes.

Name: AMAZONIAN MANATEE
Description: Trichechus inunguis ([GBF ID: 2435292](https://www.gbif.org/species/2435292)), one of the four living Manatee species. Native to the Amazon river system, the amazonian manatee is a fully aquatic mammal.

Name: TOP (TOY)
Description: A toy with rounded sides, a flat top, a vertical handle and a point at the bottom that turns round and round on the point when the handle is pushed.

Name: ARTICHOKE
Description: A plant with a round mass of pointed parts like leaves surrounding its flower that are eaten as a vegetable.

Name: IRONING BOARD
Description: A board covered with cloth, usually with folding legs, on which clothes and other items can be made smooth with an iron.

Name: ROCKING CHAIR
Description: A chair built on two pieces of curved wood so that it moves forwards and backwards when you are sitting in it.

Name: LIGHTBULB
Description: A glass or transparent container, usually rounded, with something inside that produces light when an electric current passes through it, such as an electric filament.

Name: LIGHT SWITCH
Description: A switch for turning a light on and off.

Name: ROLLING PIN
Description: A tube-shaped object, usually made from wood, metal or silicone, that is used for making dough flat and thin before cooking it.

Name: PLIERS
Description: A small tool with two handles for holding or pulling small things like nails and for cutting wire.

Name: RECORD PLAYER
Description: A machine on which records are played.

Name: SUITCASE
Description: A medium to large, rectangular container, usually with a handle, for carrying clothes and possessions while travelling.

Name: ROBOT
Description: A machine controlled by a computer that is used to perform jobs automatically.

Name: WALRUS
Description: A very large, seal-like mammal found in Arctic seas.

Name: SANDWICH
Description: A food item consisting of two or more pieces of bread with a filling between them, eaten as a light meal.

Name: SPINNING WHEEL
Description: A small domestic hand-driven or foot-driven machine for spinning thread.

Name: TOASTER
Description: An electrical appliance used for toasting, mostly bread.

Name: TRUCK
Description: A large and heavy road vehicle designed for the transportation of goods, materials, or troops.

Name: TELESCOPE
Description: An optical device used to observe distant objects and make them appear nearer, containing many lenses or curved mirrors and lenses, by which rays of lights are gathered and focused and the resulting image magnified.

Name: AMBULANCE
Description: A vehicle that is equipped for taking sick or injured people to and from hospital, especially in case of emergencies.

Name: MICROPHONE
Description: A small instrument converting sound waves into electrical energy, making it amplified or transmitted.

Name: PIRATE
Description: A person, usually working in a group, who attacks and robs ships at sea.

Name: MICROSCOPE
Description: An optical instrument for viewing very small objects such as cells, typically magnified several hundred times.

Name: JELLYFISH
Description: A marine animal, free-swimming, also known as medusa, with a jellylike saucer-shaped and nearly transparent body, and tentacles with stinging cells.

Name: BLOUSE
Description: An upper garment, which resembles a shirt, worn usually by women and girls.

Name: CIGAR
Description: A rolled bundle of dried and fermented tobacco leaves of various sizes, which is made to be smoked.

Name: CLOWN
Description: A person, artist and entertainer, who performs comedy and arts, usually wearing exaggerated makeup and a special costume, often in a circus.

Name: DINOSAUR
Description: A diverse group of reptiles, now extinct, in many species reaching an enormous size.

Name: SUBMARINE
Description: A (war)ship that can travel underwater, usually equipped with a periscope and armed.

Name: VIOLIN
Description: A small, wooden and bowed stringed musical instrument with four strings.

Name: SAXOPHONE
Description: A musical instrument of the woodwind class consisting of a curved metal tube with finger keys and a mouthpiece.

Name: LANTERN
Description: A source of light (lamp-like) with a usually transparent case protecting either the flame or the lightbulb inside, commonly with a handle by which it can be carried.

Name: SAILBOAT
Description: A type of boat propelled partly or entirely by sails, smaller than a sailing ship.

Name: BATHTUB
Description: A plastic, metal or ceramic container used for washing the whole body (bathing) when filled with water.

Name: ASHTRAY
Description: A small container or plate used for tobacco ash and cigarette ends.

Name: BABY CARRIAGE
Description: An item used for moving a baby around, also called a pram. It consists of a small bed-like structure and a frame on four wheels.

Name: DOORKNOB
Description: A handle used to open the door.

Name: IRON (PRESSING)
Description: A small house appliance used for pressing clothes.

Name: KITE (TOY)
Description: A usually triangular toy that is made of a light frame covered with cloth, paper, or plastic, which is flown in the air at the end of a long string.

Name: ELEVATOR
Description: A box-like device that moves up and down, carrying people or goods from one floor of a building/mine to another.

Name: SANDALS
Description: A light shoe consisting of a sole with straps, usually made of leather and worn when it is hot outside.

Name: SWEATER
Description: A knitted jacket or pullover, usually warm and long-sleeved.

Name: GARBAGE CAN
Description: A large container for rubbish from a house, usually made of either metal or plastic.
